State-owned enterprises and advantageous private enterprises entered the old revolutionary base area of southern Gansu.
From September 26th to 27th, in order to deepen and expand the educational achievements of the theme of "not forgetting the original intention and remembering the mission", the Central Office of Civil-Military Integration, the State Administration of Science, Technology and Industry for National Defense, and the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce jointly organized the research activity of "State-owned Enterprises and Advantageous Private Enterprises Entering the Revolutionary Base Area of Southern Jiangnan" to review the revolutionary history, pursue the red footprint, inherit the red gene, carry out the demand docking between relevant enterprises and Ganzhou City, and promote the accelerated development of the old revolutionary area.
Jin Zhuanglong, executive deputy director of the Central Office of Civil-Military Integration, Xu Lejiang, deputy director of the United Front Work Department of the CPC Central Committee, secretary of the party group and executive vice chairman of the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, Zhang Kejian, director of the State Administration of Science, Technology and Industry for National Defense, and Li Bingjun, deputy secretary of the Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee and secretary of the Ganzhou Municipal Party Committee, participated in the investigation.
The enterprises participating in the research activities include 8 military industry group companies such as China Aerospace Science and Technology Corporation, 10 private state-owned enterprises such as Hunan Rare Earth Metal Materials Research Institute, and 15 advantageous private enterprises such as EVOC Group.
During this period, the investigators visited the memorial park of the starting point of the Central Red Army's Long March, remembered the revolutionary martyrs, received revolutionary traditional education, reviewed the difficult course of the Red Army's Long March, investigated 7 enterprises and 1 testing center in Ganzhou City, held a symposium, reached 8 cooperation projects and signed on-site contracts.
At the symposium on research activities, Ganzhou City introduced its unique industrial advantages and promoted high-quality projects to the participating enterprises.
China North Industries Group Co., Ltd., China Iron and Steel Research Institute Technology Group Co., Ltd., Xi'an Tianhe Defense Technology Co., Ltd., and Jiangxi Jinli Permanent Magnet Technology Co., Ltd. made speeches on behalf of the Military Industry Group Corporation, Minkou state-owned enterprises, private enterprises, and local enterprises, respectively, saying that they will continue to strengthen the demand docking work of state-owned enterprises, advantageous private enterprises and Jiangxi Province and Ganzhou City, gradually expand the field of cooperation, help industrial transformation and upgrading, and promote the high-quality development of the old revolutionary base area.
Through this research activity, we further understand the unique industrial development advantages of the old revolutionary base area in southern Jiangnan, clarify the key tasks of economic and social development in the old revolutionary base area at this stage, and strengthen the belief of state-owned and private enterprises in serving the people and starting a business, which has an important role in promoting the transformation of the former central Soviet area in southern Jiangnan, adjusting the structure, benefiting the people's livelihood, and promoting the change of economic development quality, efficiency and power.
Beijing's market supervision department carried out comprehensive law enforcement before the holiday, and commodity prices were basically stable
Chinanews.com, Beijing, September 27 (Reporter Du Yan) In order to strengthen the pre-holiday market supervision and law enforcement, the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau inspected more than 2,000 business entities of various types on the eve of the National Day.
The inspection shows that the supply of daily necessities such as grains and oils, meat, fruits, vegetables, eggs and milk sold in the market is sufficient, the prices of commodities are basically stable, no serious violations of laws and regulations have been found, and the market operation order is generally stable.
Today, the reporter learned from the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau that the bureau carried out the "Comprehensive Law Enforcement Inspection Day" activity in the city, focusing on key areas and key areas to carry out law enforcement inspections on all elements and links such as price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and medicine, and commerce, so as to comprehensively standardize the market operation order.
According to reports, the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau's price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and drug, commerce and other five law enforcement teams coordinated and cooperated, closely cooperated, led by the heads of various law enforcement agencies, and conducted joint law enforcement inspections on randomly selected business entities in groups.
During the inspection, the law enforcement officers focused on price behavior, advertising, food safety, measurement standards, production safety systems and other contents.
The market supervision bureaus of various districts also organized joint law enforcement inspections, dispatched more than 1,600 law enforcement personnel, and inspected more than 2,000 business entities of various types.
The Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Regulation said that during the National Day, it will strengthen emergency duty, continue to carry out inspections and inspections of the market, quickly deal with all kinds of market supervision issues in accordance with the law, and seriously deal with the illegal business behaviors reported by the public once verified, so as to effectively safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of consumers.
The Confucius Institute of the Royal Academy of Sciences of Cambodia "China in My Heart" Chinese Essay Contest was announced
With the theme of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, the "China in My Heart" Chinese Essay Contest was announced at the Confucius Institute of the Royal Academy of Sciences of Cambodia on the 26th and an award ceremony was held.
Zhong Jifa, diplomat of the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia, Wei Siyu, representative of the Cambodian Chinese Council and president of the Cambodian Jiangxi Chamber of Commerce, presented awards to the winners.
According to Chai Keqing, the Chinese director of the Confucius Institute at the Royal Academy of Sciences of Cambodia, the competition lasted for two months and was open to Cambodian primary and secondary school students (including specialized students) and university students (including social workers).
Zhong Jifa, a diplomat from the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia, presented award certificates to Lin Weicai, the first prize winner of the university group, and Guo Lina, the first prize winner of the primary and secondary school group.
Chai Keqing said that the entries were divided into the university group and the primary and secondary school group, and the senior Chinese experts from Cambodia were invited to form a review committee, and through the preliminary evaluation, re-evaluation, final evaluation and other links, the final selection of the university group 1 first prize, 2 second prizes, 3 third prizes, 10 excellence awards, 1 first prize, 5 second prizes, 10 third prizes, and 20 excellence awards in the primary and secondary school group.
Lin Weicai, the first prize winner of the university group, said that he has been learning Chinese for 15 years and has had a huge impact on him.
Through the essay contest, it is to describe the benefits brought to Cambodia and the traditional friendship between China and Cambodia under the "Belt and Road" in words, and hope that the younger generation will continue to contribute to the friendship between China and Cambodia.
The picture shows the guests and the winners.
Guo Lina, the first prize winner of the primary and secondary school category, said that as an overseas Chinese, she had the opportunity to express the emotions of "China in my heart" through the words of her ancestral home and won the award, which was a different kind of excitement.
The organizer said that through the competition, it not only created a positive atmosphere for China-Cambodia relations, but also attracted more and more Cambodian students to learn Chinese and study in China.
The United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) released a report on the 26th, pointing out that Iran has begun to use advanced centrifuges to accelerate the production of enriched uranium, further violating the nuclear agreement reached with world powers in 2015.
According to comprehensive foreign media reports, the IAEA report pointed out that advanced centrifuges at Iran's Natanz Nuclear Facility (Natanz Nuclear Facility) "are accumulating or are ready to accumulate enriched uranium".
Since U.S. President Donald Trump withdrew from the nuclear deal last May and imposed sanctions on Iran, Iran has been progressively violating the limits of the 2015 nuclear deal with major powers.
The agreement stipulates that Iran can only use the first generation of IR-1 centrifuges to refine uranium.
The other signatories to the deal, Britain, China, France, Germany and Russia, have been trying to salvage the deal, but Tehran has repeatedly accused Europe of not doing enough.
According to Japan's Kyodo News Agency, on the afternoon of the 25th local time, Japanese Foreign Minister Toshimitsu Motegi held talks with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov in New York, the United States, where he visited the United States, and confirmed that he would promote the conclusion of peace treaty negotiations including the territorial issues of the four northern islands (disputed islands between Japan and Russia, known as the "four northern islands" in Japan, and the "South Kuril Islands" in Russia), and develop relations between the two countries in a wide range of fields such as politics and economy.
This was Motegi's first consultation with Russia as head of negotiations on the conclusion of a peace treaty since he took office as foreign minister.
Motegi told the Russian side that he "would like to earnestly hold consultations, including the promotion of joint economic activities [on the four northern islands]."
According to the Japanese government, the talks did not include a detailed discussion of the territorial issue.
At the Japan-Russia summit meeting in December 2018, the foreign ministers of the two countries were confirmed to accelerate negotiations as the person in charge.
At the meeting, the foreign ministers of the two countries welcomed the progress made in the consultations on common economic activities in the fields of tourism and waste disposal.
Motegi expressed his expectation that the pilot tourism project will be launched in October, saying, "We hope that it will be a successful implementation and lead to the next step." ”
In addition, the talks confirmed Lavrov's visit to Japan in November in conjunction with the G20 foreign ministers' meeting in Nagoya.
Tuiono'a was elected as the new Prime Minister of Tonga.
Nuku'alofa News: The South Pacific island nation of Tonga's parliament elected the current Minister of Finance and National Planning, Pohiwa Tuionetoa, as the new prime minister of Tonga on the 27th, replacing the former prime minister Akilisi Pohiva, who died of illness earlier this month.
ACCORDING TO THE WEBSITE OF MATANGI, A MAJOR TONGAN MEDIA OUTLET, THE TONGAN PARLIAMENT HAS A UNICAMERAL SYSTEM AND CONSISTS OF 26 MEMBERS.
In the parliamentary vote that day, Tuionotoa received 23 votes in favour, beating out rival Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Infrastructure and Tourism Semisi Sika to be elected.
Tonga is a constitutional monarchy with a separation of powers among the executive, legislature and judiciary.
Tuionetoa was also to be appointed by the king.
The next Tongan parliamentary elections will be held in 2021.
The women's volleyball team is expected to defend the World Cup ahead of schedule!
On the 27th, in the game against the Dutch women's volleyball team, the Chinese team was pulled back by the opponent after winning two games in a row, and finally defeated the Netherlands 3:1, ushering in nine consecutive wins.
The World Cup schedule is coming to an end, and although the title defense is in sight, the Chinese women's volleyball team still cannot be taken lightly in the face of the Serbian team.
In the first two games of the game with the Netherlands, the Chinese women's volleyball team performed as strong as ever, winning 25:19 and 25:16 respectively, until the third game, when the team encountered a setback.
The Dutch women's volleyball team strengthened the aggressiveness of the serve when it was behind, and the Chinese team's pass was impacted, coupled with the girls' eagerness to attack, and the mistakes began to increase, and finally the opponent pulled back a city at 21:25.
After the game, Lang Ping also pointed out in an interview: "In the third game, we gave away about 8 points because of mistakes. ”
Of course, the strength of the Dutch women's volleyball team should not be underestimated, and the Chinese women's volleyball team was also prepared for difficulties before the game, although it lost a game, everything was still in Lang Ping's hands, "It is normal to win or lose games with strong teams, and it is normal to play five games, so we told the players to be focused," Lang Ping said.
In the fourth game, the players actively adjusted their state, and Zhang Changning was full of firepower on the offensive end, scoring 8 points in a single game, making a great contribution to the team's victory.
So far, there are only two rounds left in the 11 rounds of confrontation, although the Chinese women's volleyball team has touched the championship trophy with one hand, but it did sound the alarm for the Chinese women's volleyball team in the game against the Dutch team: the more critical the moment, the more we must go all out.
In another game on the 27th, the Russian and American women's volleyball teams played 5 games, and the United States team failed to take all three points from the opponent.
All kinds of situations are developing in favor of the Chinese women's volleyball team.
However, although the Serbian team is all absent from the six main players this time, it does not mean that they will easily give the three points to the Chinese team.
Judging from the current form of the standings, the Serbian team has basically missed the medal, which means that they can "travel light" in the game against the Chinese women's volleyball team, put down their burdens and go all out to impact the opponent, while the Chinese team is under pressure to win the championship, and the state may fluctuate.
In addition, the substitute Serbian team is not a lamb to be slaughtered, in the previous battle with the Netherlands, the two sides fought 5 rounds, and the Serbian second team finally reversed the Netherlands' all-main lineup 3:2, which shows the depth of its lineup.
Before the start of the third stage of the game, Lang Ping also said that the Dutch and Serbian teams are not easy to deal with: "The game in Osaka will be very difficult, and we still have to prepare carefully as always. ”
Now the horn of defending the title has sounded, and the game has truly entered the "white-hot stage".
In terms of strength and lineup, the Chinese women's volleyball team is above the opponent, but at the last critical juncture, it depends on whether the girls of the women's volleyball team can play at a normal level and release themselves on the field.
The University of Macau (UM) today (27 October) held the "2nd Macao Stem Cell Symposium", attracting more than 100 experts and scholars from the United States, Singapore, Mainland, Hong Kong and Macao and other countries and regions engaged in the field of "external stem cell" research to share and discuss the latest technologies and developments in stem cell research with teachers and students of Macao universities.
UM Vice President (Research) Ge Wei said that stem cell research is of medical value and one of the University's key research projects, and that the symposium will help promote research and development in the field of stem cells in Macao.
Ge Wei said that as a leading international comprehensive university on the west coast of the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area, UM is committed to becoming a talent training base and innovation center on the west coast of the Greater Bay Area, contributing to the innovation and development of the Greater Bay Area.
The symposium brought together stem cell research experts from home and abroad to share the latest technologies, which will help promote stem cell research and development in Macao.
Dean of the Faculty of Health Sciences at UM Deng Chuxia said that in recent years, UM has continuously strengthened its research innovation and translation, and the number and quality of papers have also increased significantly, and the University has also achieved fruitful results in stem cell research.
At the meeting, a number of well-known scholars shared cutting-edge knowledge and cutting-edge technology in stem cell research.
Ji Weizhi, academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and dean of the School of Primate Translational Medicine of Kunming University of Science and Technology in Yunnan Province, explained the process and molecular mechanism of monkey and human embryos in vitro using a 3D culture system; Jing Naihe, a researcher at the Shanghai Institute of Biochemical Cell of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, explained the spatiotemporal changes of cell lineage and tissue changes after implantation of mouse embryos from the single-cell and molecular levels; and Wang Yong, a professor at Pennsylvania State University, showed how to use biomaterial hydrogels to simulate stem cell micronests for survival and delivery.
Associate Dean (Research) of the Faculty of Health Sciences at UM Xu Renhe, Assistant Dean Chen Guokai and Associate Professor Wang Chunming of the Institute of Chinese Medical Sciences at UM also presented their latest publications.
The 2nd Macao Stem Cell Symposium was organized by the Faculty of Health Sciences of the University of Macau, co-organized by the Institute of Chinese Medical Sciences of the University of Macau and the State Key Laboratory of Chinese Quality Research of the Macau University of Science and Technology.
There were 11 academic presentations in the symposium, including embryonic development and tissue generation, translational medicine, mechanism research and translational application of stem cells, biomaterials and applications, etc.
The seminar was held in a lively atmosphere with participants actively discussing and sharing the latest research and perspectives on related technologies.
Mr Tsui said that the symposium provided a platform for stem cell experts in the Greater Bay Area and other regions to exchange ideas and collaborate, as well as a valuable learning opportunity for students.
