On September 24th, more than 100 disabled people from Changsha were invited to board the Star of Orange Island cruise ship to enjoy the magnificent scenery of the Xiangjiang River and celebrate the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
Most of the more than 100 people with disabilities who participated in the event were boarding the ship for the first time.
Zhao Zhengang, 56, is a disabled man who rarely goes out because of his limited movement on his feet.
He said: "Today, I took a cruise for the first time, and I was very excited and unforgettable to enjoy the magnificent waves of the Xiangjiang River up close and feel the pulse of Changsha's development. ”
Volunteers from the Changsha Fukang Social Work Service Center and the Blue Sky Rescue Team provided meticulous services to the disabled.
Especially for clients with severe physical disabilities, volunteers will carry them on their backs on board and on the cruise.
The relevant person in charge of Fukang Social Work Service Center said that in the past 70 years, with the support of the party and the government, the cause of the disabled in Changsha has continued to develop and progress, and more and more disabled people have truly become participants, contributors and enjoyers of social and economic development.
