However, if the hero walks around, it also seems to be as ordinary as you and me.
Yuan Longping, who devoted himself to rice research, bred good varieties and cultivated all over the world, so that more than one billion Chinese people no longer had the risk of hunger, and made great contributions. One pot, only one thing in his life, nibbling on cold steamed buns in the deep mountains of Guizhou, no different from the old man in the village; Zhou Ruchang, a red scholar, a village boy who is enlightened very late, still looks like a child when he is old, he has studied both Chinese and Western, with a messy white hair, and likes to laugh when he talks about learning; Qin Yi, a film artist who is popular with half the sky, is over 90 years old, and he still bumps six or seven hours a day on the plateau in order to rehearse the play, and is willing to play an unknown old maid in "The Legend of the Demon Cat"...
