For example, "China's Sky Eye", now it seems, is a myth.
In the 90s of the last century, China's scientific and technological circles were still struggling to climb, and novelist Liu Cixin had not yet started writing "The Three-Body Problem".
At that time, the most powerful "eye" was the single-sided aperture radio telescope in the valley of the island of Puerto Rico in the United States, Arecibo, with a diameter of 350 meters, which was considered to be the "unsurpassable" of the world's largest.
At that time, the diameter of China's radio telescopes was less than one-tenth of that of others.
