The 500-meter-diameter "eye in the sky" was opened, and China made a "large-scale scientific project that has no precedent to follow" and is unique in the world.
Therefore, the "Eye of the Sky" is remarkable, the Nanrendong are remarkable, and the Republic of China with a large tolerance and a lofty vision is remarkable.
With the trust of the country and the goodwill of the people, Nanrendong has the opportunity to become the soul of the country and the heart and soul of the people.
There are young talents and white-haired heroes walking by kindly, and there are people applauding softly on the roadside, such a country is very beautiful and harmonious.
Garbage classification education first entered Jilin kindergarten The concept of environmental protection starts from the baby
On the 27th, a kindergarten in Jilin City, Jilin Province carried out a garbage classification education class to teach children to distinguish recyclable garbage and other types of garbage.
It is reported that this is the first time that garbage classification has entered the local early childhood education classroom.
A few days ago, nine departments of Jilin Province jointly issued the "Jilin Province to promote the classification and treatment of prefecture-level urban solid waste work plan".
In 2019, on the basis of the pilot project of compulsory classification of domestic waste in Changchun, the province decided to carry out domestic waste classification in prefecture-level cities.
Jilin City is one of them.
We hope that through this activity, we can achieve the effect of children driving families and kindergartens driving society, and advocate the concept of environmental protection.
Liu Lijuan, executive director of Hi Fan International Kindergarten, who held the event, said.
On the same day, the director read out the environmental protection proposal, hoping that garbage classification would start from children.
After performing the dance of "Low Carbon Babe", the children were divided into groups to make a small game of garbage classification.
The instructor also handed out "recyclable" and "other garbage" labels, and suggested that the children stick the labels to the trash can and record a small video when they get home.
Liu Lijuan introduced that the kindergarten has been advocating the concept of low-carbon and green environmental protection, and regularly opens environmental protection lectures.
Sortable garbage bins are also set up at the garbage disposal area in the park, and the categories of garbage are marked on them.
The teacher teaches the children what recyclable garbage is Photo by Cangyan
According to preliminary statistics, Jilin Province generated about 5,465,200 tons of municipal solid waste in 2018, all of which went to domestic waste disposal sites for treatment.
Among them, 3,292,900 tons were spared landfills, 2,092,300 tons were incinerated, and 80,100 tons were treated by comprehensive utilization technology.
After years of efforts, all cities and counties in the province have the ability to treat domestic waste harmlessly.
In the "Jilin Province Work Plan for Promoting the Classification and Treatment of Prefecture-level Municipal Domestic Waste", it is clearly required to carry out in-depth activities such as garbage classification into campuses, teaching materials, and classrooms, and strengthen the interaction between students and parents through the creation of garbage classification songs, songs, comics, micro-videos and other works, so as to achieve the effect of "educating a child, influencing a family, driving a community, and cultivating a generation of new people".
