Pro-establishment members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) signed a joint petition against the US Hong Kong-related bill
Some pro-establishment members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region issued a joint statement on the 27th, expressing strong opposition to the passage of the "Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act of 2019" by the Foreign Affairs Committees of the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States Congress.
The statement, co-signed by 40 pro-establishment legislators, said that Hong Kong currently enjoys the rights conferred by the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, including maintaining the status of a free trade port and a separate customs territory, signing and implementing bilateral and multilateral agreements with different countries and regions around the world in the name of "Hong Kong, China" in various fields such as economy, finance, shipping, trade, communications, tourism, culture and sports.
These rights are not conferred by any foreign government or legislature.
All along, Hong Kong has strictly adhered to international agreements, international rules, laws and business ethics, conducted business with different countries and regions, and participated in co-operation in many related fields.
The statement said that the move by the Foreign Affairs Committees of the US Senate and House of Representatives to pass the relevant bill is not necessary, but is only in response to the call of its agents to bring disaster to Hong Kong and as a means of grossly interfering in Hong Kong's internal affairs and gaining political bargaining chips for its agents in Hong Kong.
Pro-establishment lawmakers expressed deep regret and strong opposition to this move by the US Congress.
The statement pointed out that Hong Kong is an important trading partner of the United States and the largest source of trade surpluses.
Hong Kong's excellent rule of law, fair and free business environment, and clean society make it a good location for American businessmen to do business.
If the US Congress passes this bill, in addition to striking at Hong Kong and the interests of the United States itself, it will also make Sino-US relations worse, without any benefit and harming others and itself.
The statement said that Hong Kong will, as always, unswervingly implement the principle of "one country, two systems", continue to enjoy the rights conferred by the Basic Law, and earnestly fulfill its obligations.
In the past, present and future, Hong Kong will continue to make its due contribution to the international community and international commerce and trade.
According to a report by the European Times on the 26th, the two houses of the French parliament will discuss immigration policy reform next week.
French President Emmanuel Macron recently claimed that France cannot "accept everyone", but at the same time it must strive to "properly accept".
According to the report, Macron is trying to find a compromise on immigration matters to slow the impact of the upcoming debate.
Recently, Macron said in an interview during the general debate of the United Nations General Assembly in New York, USA, that he hopes to have a real "two-pronged" approach to migration policy, finding a balance between humanitarianism and efficiency.
"If France wants to be able to accept [immigrants] properly, it cannot accept everyone", Macron said.
Macron outlined four priorities for migration policy: the granting of asylum status to refugees in need of protection as soon as possible, the more efficient integration of migrants, the reception and protection of all migrants entering French territory, and the more efficient resettlement of people who have entered France illegally and are not fit to stay.
Whether illegal immigrants should be protected by the "National Medical Assistance" (AME) system has been the most discussed topic in the past.
Macron said he wanted to be able to "assess" the system, but not to eliminate it, but to limit it.
After Macron's remarks, Le Pen, the leader of the far-right "National Rassembled", tweeted that Macron's statement was "empty talk".
Senate President Raschel, a member of the right-wing Republican Party, also said that immigration policy should be discussed in a "moderate" but "realistic" way, indirectly criticizing Macron.
Leftist Socialist MP Valau believes that France should "accept more and better" on the issue of immigration, and criticizes Macron for "manipulating" the issue.
The report pointed out that the new version of the "Asylum and Immigration Law" has been enacted for a year, and it has led to differences of opinion within the ruling party, but at the same time it has not been able to appease the opposition parties on the right.
In the next 2022 election, the topic of migration policy will once again be the focus of attacks on the far right, and Macron will need to do something on this issue, but at the same time risk angering the left wing within the ruling party.
According to reports, the lower house of the French National Assembly will debate the immigration policy from September 30, and the Senate will debate it from October 2.
There are signs that China's A-shares are ushering in a "buyback wave", and many listed companies have taken out "real money" to buy back company shares.
According to the statistics of Oriental Wealth, a financial data service provider, as of the 27th, the total amount of repurchase of A-share listed companies in 2019 has exceeded 100 billion yuan (RMB, the same below), far exceeding the data of the same period in previous years and setting a record high in the amount of A-share share repurchase funds.
In this regard, Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Maikerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said that the overall valuation of the A-share market this year is low, and the repurchase of shares at a relatively low price is conducive to the improvement of the efficiency of the use of funds by listed companies, and also reflects the willingness of listed companies to actively manage market value and abundant cash flow, which is conducive to boosting investor confidence.
In addition, the continuous improvement of the share repurchase system has also promoted the active development of share repurchase by listed companies.
For example, at the beginning of this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange issued detailed implementation rules for listed companies to repurchase shares, providing detailed share repurchase norms and guidelines for listed companies.
According to media statistics, since the beginning of this year, the listed companies that have implemented the repurchase plan are mainly concentrated in the infrastructure industry, the real estate industry, the information technology industry and the electronic equipment manufacturing industry.
In addition, judging from the amount of repurchase payments, there are 6 listed companies with a repurchase amount of more than 1 billion yuan this year.
Among them, the first place is Yili shares, whose repurchase amount exceeds 5 billion yuan.
What is the impact on the market for listed companies to buy back shares?
Zhao Xijun, deputy dean of the School of Finance and Economics of Chinese University, said in an interview with a reporter from China News Agency that on the one hand, the buyback shows that the listed company has strong economic strength and a good financial situation, and has the ability to maintain the stability of the stock price and give investors confidence; on the other hand, it also shows that the listed company and its controlling shareholder are responsible for the company, the market and investors.
The former is based on the company's good operating performance, while the latter requires the listed company and its controlling shareholders to have high quality.
For the capital market, these are the core basic elements.
The repurchase of shares by listed companies is conducive to boosting investor confidence and supporting the stock prices of listed companies.
In addition, according to the calculation of the research report of Orient Securities, according to the estimated number of stock repurchases set by A-share listed companies since the beginning of this year, as well as the average transaction price of repurchased shares, the incremental funds brought by the repurchase of shares to the A-share market this year are expected to exceed 150 billion yuan.
It took nearly two months to complete the restoration of the large-scale mural "Tianhou Holy Miracle Map" of Tianjin Tianhou Temple, a national key cultural preservation unit, on the 26th, and will be reopened to the public during this year's National Day.
"The Sacred Miracle of the Queen of Heaven" is a large-scale traditional mural that comprehensively reflects the life of Mazu.
With the approval of the relevant state departments, it was drawn by Cai Changkui, the former director of the Tianjin Folk Museum (Tianhou Temple), from 1991 to 1994.
It is understood that this mural is painted on the south and north palace walls of the main hall of Tianhou Temple, with a total length of 32 meters, a height of 2.6 meters, divided into two parts, with more than 30 stories such as the birth of the Queen of Heaven, crossing the sea by seat, and ascending to heaven by feather, 358 characters reproduce the life deeds of Mazu.
Cai Changkui said that in recent years, Tianjin has been rainy in summer and dry in winter, which has led to the cracking of the murals, which account for 60% of the entire mural area.
In order to protect and rescue the murals of Mazu's deeds, the Management Committee of Ancient Culture Street in Nankai District, Tianjin and Tianhou Temple launched the restoration project of the main hall of Tianhou Temple and the murals in the palace.
The restoration project was led by Cai Changkui and invited four famous Chinese painters to participate.
The restoration work is based on the principle of 'repairing the old as the old', and at the same time, some parts of the original mural have been adjusted, and the original imperfect parts of the mural have been supplemented and restored.
In the restoration, we have also made innovations and experiments in color, materials, pen and ink, etc.
After restoration, the style, spirituality, spirit and artistic style of the original mural have been maintained.
Tianhou Temple was built in 1326, formerly known as Tianfei Palace, commonly known as Niangniang Palace, after many reconstructions, it is the oldest building complex in Tianjin urban area, and it is also one of the earliest existing Mazu temples in China.
On September 25, the commissioning ceremony of Beijing Daxing International Airport was held.
The shape of the terminal building of Beijing Daxing International Airport means "phoenix spreading its wings" and is known as the first of the "Seven Wonders of the New World".
At present, Beijing Capital International Airport is already in a state of overload, carrying 100 million+ passengers last year, becoming the second airport in the world to handle more than 100 million passengers annually after Atlanta Airport in the United States.
It is estimated that by 2022, the passenger throughput of Beijing Daxing International Airport will reach 45 million, with international flights accounting for 20%; By 2025, passenger throughput will reach 72 million, and the proportion of international flights is expected to reach 30%.
As a "new country", how cool is it?
Beijing Daxing International Airport is located between Daxing District, Beijing and Guangyang District, Langfang City, Hebei Province, with a straight-line distance of 46 kilometers from Tiananmen Square, making it the world's largest new airport.
The roof of the terminal is covered with a steel projection area of 180,000 square meters, the size of 25 standard football fields.
Beijing Daxing International Airport is the first terminal in the world to have two arrivals and two departures levels – F1-F4 for international arrivals, domestic arrivals, domestic departures, and international departures.
The double-decker bridge connecting the expressway and the airport outside the terminal corresponds to the F3 and F4 of the terminal building respectively - the upper floor of the international departure and the two floors of the domestic departure.
The maiden flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport ushered in the era of Beijing's "dual airports".
Up to now, a total of 66 airlines are interested in entering Beijing Daxing International Airport, including 20 domestic airlines, 46 Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan and foreign airlines, and the flight schedules of various airlines have been approved.
In the 2019 winter and spring season, Beijing Daxing International Airport is expected to open 116 routes, including 101 domestic routes and 15 international routes, covering 112 destinations around the world, including 97 domestic destinations and 15 international destinations.
This forms a "dual-hub" airport pattern with coordinated development, moderate competition and world-class competitiveness with Beijing Capital International Airport, which not only alleviates the operational pressure of the capital airport's saturated capacity, but also better meets the urgent needs of the rapid growth of air transport in Beijing and surrounding areas, and effectively enhances the international competitiveness of China's civil aviation industry.
In order to ensure efficiency and quality, Beijing Daxing International Airport fully considers the relationship between geographical location, airport and surrounding airspace and operating environment, and the airport runway adopts an "omnidirectional" layout for the first time in China, adopts the world's largest air traffic control automation system, and establishes China's largest terminal control area, which can maximize the efficiency of aviation operations.
For the first time in China, an airport of this size has adopted a localized automatic baggage handling and information management system, and adopted an innovative baggage transmission mode to improve the efficiency of the baggage system.
The maiden flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport indicates that the phoenix spreads its wings and takes off coolly.
The new airport, which has created more than 40 international and domestic firsts and has a localization rate of more than 98%, will have a direct and indirect economic impact on the industries in the surrounding areas and inject vitality into Beijing's economic development.
MCA is tentatively scheduled to hold a congress in November to reduce the age of joining the party to 16 years old
