With the approval of the National Assembly to lower the voting age in the general election, MCA announced that the 66th Central Congress to be held this year will put forward proposals to amend the party constitution, including lowering the age of MCA to join the party from the current 18 to 16 years old.
MCA president Datuk Seri Wee Ka Siong said that the MCA Central Committee was originally scheduled to hold the Central Congress on November 2 and 3 this year, but due to the by-election for the Tanjung Piai parliamentary seat, the date of the congress may be changed.
He said that since the Election Committee will only meet on October 1 to finalize the nomination date and polling day for the Tanjung Piai national seat, they will meet the next day, October 2, to discuss whether to change the date of this year's Central Congress.
He also explained that the purpose of the Central Committee meeting yesterday (26th) was to finalize the date of the congress and amend the party constitution, but it just happened that the Bumiputera Solidarity Party Tanjung Piai MP Datuk Mohd Fali passed away due to illness, so he joined the agenda of the by-election for this national seat.
Wang Boxiang, former secretary of the Shouguang County Party Committee of Shandong Province - Qiang County Rich People Pure Heart-Xinhuanet
Wang Boxiang, a native of Shouguang, Shandong, was born in February 1943, joined the work in 1967, and successively served as secretary of the township party committee, secretary of the county party committee, mayor and other positions.
In 1986, Wang Boxiang served as the secretary of the Shouguang County Party Committee in Shandong Province, which was a poor county in Weifang at that time.
During the five years of Shouguang's tenure, Wang Boxiang had the heart of serving the people and concentrated on three things: one was to promote the industrialization of vegetables, the second was to develop the saline-alkali beach in Shoubei, and the third was to lay the foundation for the industrial turnaround, so that Shouguang people would bulge their pockets and waists.
Shouguang farmers have a tradition of growing vegetables, and they have also learned the lesson of growing vegetables.
In the early 80s of the last century, Shouguang farmers planted a bumper harvest of vegetables but could not sell them, and they rotted in the ground.
Wang Boxiang's investigation found that the key to grasping vegetables is to do a good job in circulation.
Shouguang took the lead in building a vegetable wholesale market, which opened the prelude to the development of market economy.
Party members and cadres must take the lead, mess up, and bear all the losses in the county.
In 1989, with the support of Wang Boxiang, 17 party members including Wang Leyi of Sanyuan Zhu Village set up 17 winter warming vegetable greenhouses, and 17 "double 10,000 households" emerged in the village that year.
Subsequently, the county set up a promotion group, under the mobilization of Wang Boxiang, Wang Leyi toured and guided in various towns and towns, and promoted more than 5,000 vegetable greenhouses in the first year, and then the vegetable greenhouses were promoted to the whole county and even the whole country like a prairie fire.
For thousands of years, 1.6 million acres of land in Shoubei have been shallow tidal flats in addition to saline-alkali flats.
Life is very difficult for the local people.
Shounan has a vegetable greenhouse, what to do in Shoubei?
Wang Boxiang organized more than 100,000 people to engage in a general battle, and set up camp on the barren alkali beach, which lasted forty or fifty days.
Wang Boxiang and the leading cadres in the county eat and live on the construction site, pushing carts and carrying burdens like migrant workers, eating and sleeping in the open, and the people all stretch their thumbs when they see them, and admire them in their hearts... At that time, Shoubei developed 150,000 acres of shrimp ponds, 200,000 acres of salt pans, 600,000 acres of cotton fields, and developed a "cornucopia" on the saline-alkali tidal flats.
In July 1986, Wang Boxiang participated in the Weifang Industrial Conference for the first time as the secretary of the county party committee.
During the meeting, a "comparison table of industrial economic figures in the twelve counties and urban areas of Weifang City" was issued, and at first glance, the total industrial output value, Shouguang was not bad, ranking fourth.
But if the raw salt is removed, Shouguang's pure industrial output value is only 119 million yuan, ranking third from the bottom.
Wang Boxiang led a group of more than 70 people to "change their brains" in other places.
In less than a year, the county invested 150 million yuan and launched 77 projects.
Since then, it has organized "scripture learning groups" every year to go to Shenzhen, Dongguan and Shanghai to learn from them.
Shouguang lacks enterprises, and even more entrepreneurs.
Wang Boxiang presided over a special meeting to make a decision: in the county's open selection of factory directors and managers, 40 "enterprising talents" stood out and were pushed to the front line of industry.
In 1991, Shouguang entered the ranks of the top 100 counties in the country, and Wang Boxiang was transferred to the deputy mayor of Weifang City.
What he left behind was more than 200,000 vegetable greenhouses, 1.2 million acres of cotton fields, salt pans, and shrimp ponds, 4,854 enterprises, and more than 100,000 "10,000 households", and a cadre team recognized by the people. The people of Shouguang still affectionately call him "our secretary of Boxiang".
On September 26, local time, State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi presided over the Foreign Ministers' Meeting of China and African Security Council members at the United Nations Headquarters in New York.
Present at the meeting were Foreign Minister Tano of Côte d'Ivoire, Foreign Minister Oyono of Equatorial Guinea, Foreign Minister Pandor of South Africa, Foreign Minister Carra, and Foreign Minister Geshinawi of Tunisia, who are currently members of the Security Council.
Wang Yi put forward a four-point proposal on strengthening cooperation between China and Africa in the Security Council.
First, we need to unite to build strength.
The biggest challenge in the current international situation is unilateralism, the direct consequence of which is that the basic norms governing international relations have been challenged, the role of the United Nations has been impacted, and the interests of the vast number of developing countries, including African countries, and small and medium-sized countries have been undermined.
To meet this challenge, China and Africa need to join hands and stand shoulder to shoulder.
In the Security Council, the three African countries speak with one voice, and the weight of the focus is not just three votes, but the entire African continent.
If China and Africa stand together, it will not just have four votes, but will lead other countries to follow suit, influence and shape the agenda of the Security Council.
Since 2018, China has established a "3+1" coordination mechanism with African members of the Security Council, and we should make full use of this coordination mechanism.
Second, resolve disputes through negotiation.
China has always advocated the political settlement of hotspot issues, and Africa has a good tradition of consultation and the experience of successful mediation by African regional and subregional organizations.
Many of the complex issues on the Council's agenda, particularly the African hotspots, are mostly the bane of colonialism, while others are directly related to external factors.
We should make good use of Chapter VI of the Charter of the United Nations and give full play to the role of the United Nations in mediation and mediation.
Third, we need to seek self-improvement through self-reliance.
African countries and peoples know best about Africa's problems, and Africa has the ability and wisdom to solve its own problems.
When dealing with Africa's hotspot issues, the Security Council should focus on listening to and respecting Africa's wishes, should play the role of regional and subregional organizations, and should encourage and support endogenous solutions from Africa.
China is ready to strengthen coordination with Africa and firmly promote the capacity-building of Africa's independent peace operations.
Fourth, we need to rely on development to address the fundamentals.
China and the vast number of African countries are developing countries, and we should persist in putting economic and social development first and support each other in the development path they have chosen.
China is ready to closely align the Belt and Road Initiative with the African Union's Agenda 2063, the United Nations 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development and the development strategies of African countries, so as to help African countries enhance their development capacity and eliminate the root causes of conflict.
Together, we need to push the United Nations to increase its investment in Africa's development.
With the resurgence of the Ebola outbreak in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), China has made and will continue to provide all-out assistance, providing manpower and material assistance to the best of its ability, and is ready to coordinate actions with African countries, mobilize the United Nations and the World Health Organization (WHO) to increase assistance, and give full play to the role of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (MINUSTRIA).
The neonatal department and other relays to save the lives of the little ones.
Thrilling!
The mother of the second child had an early seizure, and on the way to the hospital in a hurry, a 32-week premature baby was born in the passenger seat of the father's car.
Fortunately, obstetricians and neonatologists dealt with it in time and relayed the little life.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th, and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatology departments of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, and the other two were born in the 120 ambulance, both of which were 29-week premature babies.
Ms. Cheng is a pregnant mother of a second child, at 7 o'clock in the morning on September 19, she felt a little pain in her stomach, thinking that she was 32 weeks pregnant, and the first child was also born prematurely, she packed her belongings and prepared to take a shower and go directly to the hospital.
After 9:30 a.m., Ms. Cheng packed up and asked her husband to drive from Xu Dong's home to the hospital.
Unexpectedly, not long after the car drove out of the house, the baby couldn't wait to be born in the passenger seat of his father's car.
Twenty minutes later, Ms. Cheng and her baby finally arrived at the Obstetrics and Gynecology Building of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital.
When the hospital security saw the panicked couple and the baby, they immediately notified the obstetric delivery room, and the deputy chief physician Zhang Huan and other 4 doctors and midwife Liu Yanyan rushed downstairs with the delivery bag and umbilical cord coil.
At that time, the mother was half-lying in the passenger seat of the car, with amniotic fluid and blood under her, and a baby boy was next to her, with an umbilical cord attached. ”
Zhang Huan inquired and learned that the baby was a 32-week premature baby, and the parents did not have time to cover the child on the way.
Liu Yanyan hurried to the co-pilot to treat the baby's umbilical cord, Zhang Huan got into the cab, quickly opened the birth bag, wrapped the child with several layers of warmth with the treatment towel and the cloth of the delivery bag, and cleaned the respiratory tract for the newborn (as shown in the picture), and then carried the baby up to the neonatal department on the 12th floor.
After learning the news, the neonatal doctors immediately rushed to the nurses' station to rescue the premature baby on the spot.
At that time, the baby's face was purple, there was suffocation and lack of oxygen, the doctor immediately intubated him, and in less than a minute, the baby's heartbeat was restored, and the skin color gradually returned to ruddy, and the recovery was successful.
After being admitted to the hospital, the 32-week-old baby was put on an invasive ventilator, and after continuous rescue, his breathing was stable, and he was successfully weaned the next day.
After a week of treatment, the baby's vital signs are stable, his breathing is smooth, and he has begun to feed a small amount.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th, and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatology departments of the hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, and the other two were born in the 120 ambulance, both of which were premature babies at 29 weeks, and are currently being actively treated in the neonatal department.
Sun Guoqiang, director of the obstetrics department of the Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital, said that in recent years, the provincial maternal and child children have received many babies born on the subway and in private cars, and this situation may threaten the life safety of mothers and children if they are not handled well.
Director Sun reminded that once pregnant mothers have abdominal pain, broken water, redness and other phenomena, they should come to the hospital immediately.
In case of delivery at home or on the road, the mother should try to lie flat as much as possible, and put a blanket under the buttocks to prevent the baby's head from hitting the ground after delivery, and the child should be kept warm immediately after delivery, and sent to the nearest hospital as soon as possible.
