Witness the 10 years of digital China's "cloud rise" in Yunqi Town - Xinhuanet
If we take the 2009 local website forum as the starting point, the 2019 Apsara Conference held in Hangzhou from 25 to 27 has gone through a full decade.
From the concept of "foggy in the clouds" to the practice of "going to the cloud", big data and cloud computing have become one of the core technologies supporting China's economic development, social management and public services in the past 10 years.
In the photovoltaic cell workshop of Chint New Energy in Haining, Zhejiang, there has recently been a new "colleague" loaded with Alibaba Cloud artificial intelligence next to the quality inspector.
