"In some construction sites, it is estimated that more than half of the overage migrant workers are employed.
Where to find young workers now?
I don't want to use so many 'old people' on the construction site, there is no way. ”
Recently, Zou Kui, who has been working as an engineering contractor in the construction industry for many years, lamented that there are many over-age migrant workers (over the retirement age) on the construction site.
Recently, the author's university has carried out a rain and sewage diversion project, and there are many migrant workers on campus.
Overage migrant workers go out to work not because they are "idle", but because they "can't be idle", and have the helplessness and hardship of "having to do this" -- whether it is saving money to solve their pension and medical problems, or helping their children, they all drive these old people who should be "idle" to continue to work hard.
The "old age dependent" of over-age migrant workers is not as easy as we imagined.
When these migrant workers complete their "life tasks", their money bags have been emptied and even have a lot of debts, and most of them lack wealth accumulation.
In order not to drag down their children and to accumulate more wealth for themselves, many migrant workers insist on "working until they can't do it".
Many of the new generation of migrant workers from the "post-80s", "post-90s" and even "post-00s" are unwilling to engage in the secondary industry or low-end service industry with difficult conditions and high labor intensity, resulting in a structural "labor shortage".
Due to the lack of a skill, and the decline in physical function and working ability, many over-age migrant workers are engaged in work with high intensity, low income, high risk, and low security.
Being able to work day by day is a day, and being able to earn a little more is a little bit, and the survival plight of over-age migrant workers behind "can't be idle" cannot be ignored and ignored.
In addition to their "self-salvation", solving the problem of arrears of wages and wage bargaining, improving labor protection, reducing safety risks, increasing labor income, and improving the living conditions of over-age migrant workers are also inseparable from the institutional protection and humanistic care of the public sector.
Some scholars have pointed out that over-age migrant workers are less likely to rely on returning home to farm to solve their pension and medical problems, and they must find other ways to support their families.
Understanding the helplessness and strength of over-age migrant workers will help us better understand the love and pain of over-age migrant workers.
Seeing the backs of over-age migrant workers, hearing their sighs, and trying to make them truly "rely on the elderly" when they return to the countryside, it is necessary for the public sector, the market and society to share responsibilities in a benign interaction, and to work together.
Chemezov said that Russia will not export such systems in the next five years, because "it will first supply its own army, after which it will be produced for export."
This approach is fully in line with international practice.
The main producers of weapons and military equipment always ensure their own defense needs first, and only then do they process export orders.
Earlier, the Deputy Commander-in-Chief of the Russian Aerospace Forces, General Yuri Glekhov, said that the development of the system was nearing completion.
The S-500 system was developed by the "Diamond-Antai" air and space defense Kang Zeen.
This is a new generation of air defense systems with a working principle for destroying ballistic and aerodynamic targets.
The main role of the S-500 is to intercept medium-range ballistic missiles, which can intercept missiles with a range of less than 3500 km.
In addition, according to some information, the S-500 can destroy hypersonic cruise missiles, as well as aircraft, almost all types of unmanned aircraft, hypersonic missiles that exceed the speed of sound by 5 times, and even targets located in near space.
This weapon can also be integrated into a unified network with other air defense systems, in particular, the S-400 system, which is very important from a defense point of view.
Sergei Chemezov expressed special concern about the S-400.
He said that the system is currently in great demand in the world, but the Russian army also needs it, including in the Arctic.
The S-400 air defense system entered service with the Arctic air defense regiment.
According to information from September 15, the modification of the S-400 anti-aircraft missile system of the Arctic air defense regiment of Novaya Zemlya has been completed.
This is not the militarization of Russia in the Arctic.
According to the Russian Ministry of Defense, this is a process that is fully within the planned transition to more advanced defense tools in the northern strategic direction.
According to the press service of the Russian Northern Fleet, "With the transition to the new S-400 air defense system, the controllable airspace in the Arctic region has increased significantly. ”
It is very important that, according to military assessments, the use of this system in the Far North and the Arctic is successful.
Officers and men of the air defense regiment were trained on the new system and were ready to go on combat duty.
Previously, the S-300 long-range air defense system was equipped there, and now part of it remains.
When it comes to air defense systems, they must have weapons capable of destroying all kinds of air targets, whether they are high-speed targets flying at the outer altitude layer or "fish in the net" that are close to the protected facilities.
According to open sources, the S-400 Triumph system, developed by Golden Diamond-Antai Aerospace Defense Kang Tseen, is designed to attack strategic and tactical aircraft, ballistic missiles, hypersonic targets and other air attack weapons.
This weapon can attack aerodynamic targets at a range of 400 km and shoot down ballistic targets at a distance of 4.8 km per second at a distance of 60 km.
Russia has never concealed that it will deploy additional air defense forces in the far north to ensure the security of its airspace along the northern sea route.
Not so long ago, the first batch of 12 anti-aircraft missile systems "Tor - M2DT" was delivered to the Russian Arctic, they are enough to form an air defense battalion to strengthen the air defense system of the Arctic region.
The Russian Ministry of Defense said at that time that the Arctic "Thor" unit would be expanded to a full brigade-level formation in the future.
Together with the S-400 long-range systems newly deployed to Novaya Zemlya and the Kola Peninsula and the Pantsir-SA short-range systems deployed in the far north, these advanced anti-aircraft weapons are a powerful defense of Russia's polar skies.
It will be difficult for enemy aircraft, helicopters and drone missiles to break through this defense.
According to the idea of the Russian government, the flagship store will become a platform for Russian manufacturers to place their goods, avoiding the complicated and lengthy process of opening their own store.
Rospindo, the operator of Russian stores, focuses on the sale of Russian goods in China.
Rospinduo has online stores on China's largest trade platforms such as Tmall, JD.com, 1688, Pinduoduo, ShouQ, and Wechat, as well as its own online platform Epinduo.com and retail chain stores of Russian goods.
The Russian Export Center will work with Rospindo to develop store marketing strategies and participation criteria, as well as screen companies with products on virtual shelves.
The store is scheduled to open by the end of this year and have products from at least 10 Russian manufacturers on the shelves.
According to the Russian Export Center, the total number of visits to Chinese e-commerce platforms is as high as 1 billion per month.
At the same time, food exports to China have been growing steadily since 2014 and exceeded $1 billion in 2018.
Currently, Alibaba Group will also open pilot stores to sell goods from New Zealand, Malaysia and Singapore within the framework of its global import strategy.
According to Alexei Kozhevnikov, the new store will display the goods of enterprises with sales of at least 500 million rubles.
To be honest, my expectations are higher, sales of 500 million rubles are not enough.
We all know that Chinese consumers have a very positive attitude towards Russian goods, regarding Chinese products as high-quality and environmentally friendly. ”
Kozhevnikov said competition for Chinese consumers, who have strong purchasing power, is fierce and intensifying.
"Our goal is ambitious, to launch 500 businesses through this store within three years," he said. ”
At the same time, the platform will also list the products of companies in the Russian Far East.
Vyacheslav Cheglov, a professor at the Department of Fundamentals of Trade Policy at the Plekhanov University of Economics in Russia, said: "This is a political project that represents the image of both sides, because the Russian export center is state-owned, not private. ”
"I don't see a lot of Russian goods that are very competitive on the market. ”
He believes that the project will most likely not be actually implemented, but it will help strengthen relations between the two countries.
According to RIA Novosti, Andrey Slepnev, president of the Russian Export Center, said on the sidelines of the Eastern Economic Forum that information on the products of more than 170 Russian companies has been published on the largest international wholesale online platform Alibaba.com, which can be purchased both in China and in other countries.
In addition, there is a model of cooperation with Alibaba Group, namely a training program for Russian companies by experts from Taobao University, the first seminar of which was held in July this year.
At the second China International Import Expo in Shanghai in November this year, the Russian Export Center will also serve as an organizer of the participation of Russian companies in industry exhibitions and business projects.
A large-scale exhibition will be held in a 1,000-square-meter exhibition hall, which will also become a center for business project events, agreement signing ceremonies, presentations and meetings with representatives of Chinese companies.
About 50 applications from Russian agricultural enterprises have been received.
The press service of the Russian Export Center said: "In addition to the agricultural stand, we will definitely hold business meetings, that is, arrange direct contacts between entrepreneurs. ”
"This is another direction of our efforts to support companies and ensure that dozens of dedicated meetings are arranged for them. ”
In addition, master classes, cooking competitions and a tasting of Russian food by famous Russian chefs of the project "Discover Russian Cuisine in Shanghai" will be held.
