E-cigarettes in the United States have killed 12 cases of lung damage and reached 805.
According to the "Central News Agency", on the 26th local time, U.S. health officials said that 12 people have died from e-cigarette-related diseases in the United States, and there have been 805 cases of lung damage related to e-cigarette smoking.
The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention reportedly reported the numbers and said it had not identified the specific substance responsible for the disease.
However, most patients report using vaping products containing THC, the main compound in cannabis that affects mental status.
It is reported that the spike in lung cases is related to the purchase of contaminated e-cigarettes on the black market.
According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, the 12 deaths were reported in 10 states from California to Florida, while the 805 confirmed and suspected cases were reported from 46 states and the U.S. Virgin Islands.
In the past three weeks, India and Massachusetts have banned the sale of e-cigarettes, while New York and Michigan have banned flavored e-cigarettes.
According to the report, the Trump administration intends to ban all flavors of e-cigarette products except tobacco flavors starting in October.
When is the next bus coming?
"Internet + smart stop sign" makes you know in your heart.
On the 27th, Nanjing Intelligent Transportation and Gaode Map announced that the first batch of "Internet + smart stop signs" in the country officially landed in Nanjing, when Nanjing will have 54 bus electronic screens to be lit up, which will comprehensively upgrade the level of information service in Nanjing, improve the efficiency of bus service and the happiness of the people.
In the past, the anxious scene of waiting for the bus was played out almost every day at the bus stop.
The bus running time is difficult to predict, the bus road conditions and vehicle location along the way are difficult to know, and the pain points of bus travel need to be solved urgently, especially in some large cities, the commuting road is long, and the traffic conditions are complex during the morning and evening commuting rush hours, resulting in the punctuality rate of the bus has been difficult to guarantee.
To this end, Nanjing Smart Transportation has joined hands with AutoNavi Map to explore the new direction of "Internet + Transportation" convenient services, and launched the first batch of "Internet + Smart Stop Signs" in the country.
It is reported that the country's first batch of "Internet + smart stop signs" landed in Nanjing, integrating AutoNavi big data and AutoNavi's ETA algorithm for the estimated travel time of vehicles, and relying on the upgrade of bus electronic stop signs and mobile Internet and traffic big data, to achieve the ability of "bus smart stop board + electronic map" to release bus routes and bus estimated arrival times.
Through the "Internet + smart stop sign", Nanjing citizens can not only easily get the estimated arrival time of the bus, understand the real-time location of the bus and how many stations are still from the current station, but also intuitively grasp the bus conditions along the way through the three colors of red, orange and green, so that all the real-time situation of the bus lines passing through the station can be clear at a glance.
Thanks to the warm-hearted launch of "Internet + smart stop sign", Nanjing citizens have realized convenient and efficient bus travel methods such as "checking the location of the bus before going out, grasping the arrival time when waiting for the bus, and knowing the arrival time when taking the bus".
According to the real-time bus information of "Internet + smart stop sign", choose the most suitable travel route for yourself, and at the same time make psychological expectations and reduce the anxiety of waiting for the bus, so as to make travel more convenient and calm.
More than 30 pieces of fine cultural relics of the Summer Palace were exhibited for the first time-Xinhuanet
The reporter learned from the Beijing Summer Palace Management Office that a total of 99 sets of cultural relics were exhibited, of which more than 30 cultural relics were exhibited to the public for the first time in the Summer Palace, showing the rich collection of palace cultural relics in the Summer Palace and its traditional Fushou cultural connotation.
It is reported that the exhibition is divided into four exhibition areas: Ruiyu Jijin, Fushu Shou, Qigong Jueyi, and Fucai Zenghua, which exhibit jade bronze, ancient books and calligraphy, miscellaneous, porcelain enamel and other categories of cultural relics to the audience.
Kui Lijia, deputy director of the Cultural Relics Department of the Summer Palace Management Office, introduced that the number of high-level cultural relics in this cultural relics exhibition is large, the cultural relics are varied, and the age span of the exhibits is large.
Nearly three-thirds of the cultural relics exhibited are national first-class cultural relics and second-class cultural relics, and the age of cultural relics spans from the Shang Dynasty to the Guangxu period of the Qing Dynasty.
The Shang Dynasty Zhenggui on display is more than 3,000 years old, and is the "oldest" bronze cultural relics on display; the green jade lying cow is huge, weighing nearly 80 catties, it is carved from a whole piece of green jade, and it is very rare to preserve the good condition; the wooden table clock of the mountain stone figures, the "Nanzhai Collection Picture Book" and "Nanzhai Collection Calligraphy" are also the fine cultural relics that are exhibited to the public for the first time.
Qin Lei, deputy director of the Beijing Summer Palace Management Office, said that the cultural exhibition adheres to the spirit of "bringing cultural relics to life", relying on the gardening idea of "Fushan Shouhai" in the Summer Palace, and taking the cultural relics with the theme of "Fushou" in the garden as the carrier, so that visitors can understand the profound Fushou culture of the Summer Palace through the exhibition, promote and inherit the traditional Chinese culture, and convey the good wishes of praying for blessings and celebrating longevity.
It is reported that the exhibition will last until January 30, 2020.
Xinhua Times Commentary: Unswervingly follow our own path
The white paper "China and the World in the New Era" released on the 27th answers: Over the past 70 years, the fundamental reason for China's successful development is that under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, the Chinese people have found the correct development path of socialism with Chinese characteristics and unswervingly followed this road.
It is the choice of history and the choice of the people for China to follow a development path that suits itself.
In modern times, in an environment of poverty and weakness, internal and external troubles, generations of people with lofty ideals have sought and continued to explore the road to save the country and the people.
However, "the constitutional monarchy, the restoration of the monarchy, the parliamentary system, the multi-party system, and the presidential system have all been thought of and tried, but none of them will work." ”
It was not until the Communist Party of China and New China that Chinese people gradually opened up a path of socialism with Chinese characteristics in practice.
The path that China has embarked on is the road to the happiness of the Chinese people, the road to the rejuvenation of the Chinese nation, and the road of common development between China and other countries in the world.
It is precisely because China is on the right path that it can handle its own affairs well, become the world's second largest economy and the country that contributes the most to global economic growth, and continue to benefit the world with its own development.
As pointed out in the white paper, China's development path is in line with China's national conditions, adapts to the requirements of the times, and will show more and more bright prospects for development as the times progress.
Looking back, the Chinese people know very well how difficult it is to find a correct path; looking around the world, the Chinese people cherish this correct path even more.
Chinese understand the truth of the south orange and the north orange, and understand that what suits others is not necessarily suitable for themselves, and only what suits them is the best.
It is with this kind of self-confidence and strategic determination that China has created a miracle that has attracted worldwide attention.
In the tortuous process of mankind's progress, the "final conclusion of history" was once famous.
Today, the success of the road of socialism with Chinese characteristics has announced the end of the "final conclusion of history", the collapse of the "theory of China's collapse", and the failure of the "theory of the defeat of socialism".
China's success has boosted the confidence of developing countries in achieving national prosperity and national strength, broadened the way for developing countries to move toward modernization, and provided experience and reference for those countries and nations in the world that wish to accelerate development while maintaining their independence and take a path suited to their national conditions.
The world is colorful.
China has always respected the right of each country to choose a development path suited to its own national conditions.
China will not "import" foreign models or "export" Chinese models, but will unswervingly follow its own path, achieve its own continuous development, strengthen governance exchanges with other countries, and make due contributions to the common realization of good governance.
The Fair Work Commission found that a Foodworks supermarket owner fired a 66-year-old female worker via text message because he preferred to hire employees from Asian backgrounds, and the boss's practice was slammed as "shameful."
The committee said the way Jianbin Wang, the owner of Ms. Gail Ayton, who has worked at the Wagga store for more than 20 years, treated employees was "grossly unfair" and may have violated anti-discrimination laws.
Ms. Ayton told the committee that Mr. Wang took over the shop in 2016 and that he had been "trying to fire me" because she was not Chinese.
In this case, Peter Sams, Deputy Chairman of the Commission, conducted an internet search and found "some job advertisements posted by Mr Wang in the past at various Australian Chinese employment forums".
Among the job requirements listed for these positions, one of them says "Asian Lady Preferred" and the other says "Asian Employee Preferred".
The third post said he was "more inclined to people overseas (sic)".
Mr. Wang fired Ms. Ayton via text message in April of this year, later saying it was due to her absence from work and a small amount of cash missing from the cash register that was allegedly $5.10 to $30.
Mr. Sams alleges, however, that Mr. Wang's reasons for dismissing Ms. Ayton were weak and lacked evidence.
She has only missed one shift in three years, and the "missing amount" totals a few dollars.
He said Ms. Ayton's dismissal "had nothing to do with her conduct or performance."
He said: "It seems to me that the real motive of the respondent in dismissing him, supported by the evidence of the job advertisement posted by Mr. Wang, was that he preferred to hire employees with Asian backgrounds.
Under section 772(f) of the Fair Work Act, Mr. Wang's conduct constituted a prima facie violation of the Anti-Discrimination Act and/or the dismissal of the Applicant was unlawful. ”
Mr. Sams stated that it would not be appropriate for him to consider reinstating Ms. Ayton in view of the "appalling" treatment he had given to Ms. Ayton.
He should consider paying compensation to Ms Ayton, who is a casual worker who earns $26 an hour.
In light of the possible violations of anti-discrimination and industrial relations legislation, Sams said he would submit his ruling and documents to the commission's supervisor to consider whether Mr. Wang's conduct should be referred to another agency to investigate possible violations of state or federal law.
He states that Mr. Wang did not give Ms. Ayton any opportunity to respond to the alleged grounds for her dismissal.
He said: "In my opinion, the respondent adopted an incorrigibly unfair and biased procedure to dismiss the applicant, and Mr Wang 'waited' for this opportunity, which he believed would 'justify' the termination of employment of the applicant. ”
