In order to stabilize the company's stock price and maintain the company's image, listed companies have begun to repurchase shares frequently in the past two years, hoping to pass on the information that the company's value is undervalued to the market through directional repurchase and collective bidding transactions, so as to stabilize the stock price and enhance investor confidence.
According to data from Oriental Wealth Choice, the funds used by listed companies to repurchase shares in 2017 were 7.9 billion yuan, which soared to 51 billion yuan in 2018, and since 2019, the total amount of repurchase by A-share listed companies has exceeded 100 billion yuan, setting a new high in the amount of repurchase funds in the history of A-shares, and far exceeding the previous years.
From the perspective of the purpose of the repurchase, the company's repurchase of shares and the increase of major shareholders seem to be the same, but there are great differences in the implementation of the subject, the source of funds, the purpose of the repurchase, and the rights and interests of the stock itself.
Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Maikerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said in an interview with the "Securities Daily" reporter that in November 2018, the "Opinions on Supporting Listed Companies to Repurchase Shares" was revised for the problems existing in the current system such as the narrow scope of share repurchase, complex decision-making procedures, and imperfect inventory system.
In January this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange officially issued the "Implementation Rules for the Repurchase of Shares by Listed Companies", the introduction of these policies has broadened the sources of funds for the repurchase of listed companies, appropriately simplified the implementation procedures, guided the improvement of governance arrangements, and encouraged all kinds of listed companies to implement equity incentives or employee stock ownership plans.
After the issuance of the opinions, the operation of share repurchase by listed companies has more applicable circumstances, the repurchase process is simpler, and the enthusiasm for share repurchase is also greater.
Repurchasing shares at a relatively low position is also conducive to the listed company to improve the efficiency of the use of funds, thereby increasing the level of earnings per share, improving the return on net assets, and reducing the pressure on the company's profitability indicators.
Compared with the increase in holdings of major shareholders, the repurchase of shares by listed companies is of greater significance, which also reflects the willingness of listed companies to actively manage market value and abundant cash flow.
Xu Yang believes that the undervaluation of the stock price is the main factor in the repurchase of listed companies, and the company's stock price has not been able to reflect the company's future development prospects, so this kind of company is worthy of investors' attention, but can not blindly invest, and needs to pay attention to the financial reports and specific operations of such listed companies.
Listed companies with large-scale repurchase behavior at least show the company's development confidence and financial strength.
The data shows that nearly 1,000 listed companies have implemented share repurchases this year, and leading companies in various industries have become the main force in the repurchase market.
Ping An recently disclosed the progress of the repurchase, saying that the company has repurchased a total of 57.59 million A shares through centralized bidding transactions, accounting for 0.315% of the company's total share capital, and the total amount of funds paid is 5 billion yuan (excluding transaction costs), and the repurchased shares will be used for employee stock ownership plans, including but not limited to the long-term service plan approved by the company's general meeting of shareholders.
Yili shares have paid 5.792 billion yuan for share repurchase, and recently adjusted the use of repurchased shares, from the original plan "the repurchase of shares will be used as a source of shares for the later implementation of equity incentives" to "a total of 183 million shares, of which 152 million shares are used for the implementation of equity incentive stock sources, and the remaining 30.49 million shares will be used for cancellation to reduce the registered capital".
Yili shares said that the cancellation of part of the repurchased shares is conducive to further improving the level of earnings per share and effectively improving the return on investment of the company's shareholders.
TCL Group issued a repurchase progress announcement on September 25, showing that TCL Group has repurchased 3.59% of the company's shares in total, costing a total of 1.65 billion yuan.
The office of the board of directors of TCL Group told the "Securities Daily" reporter that the repurchased shares will be used for employee stock ownership plans, equity incentives or for the conversion of corporate bonds issued by listed companies that can be converted into shares.
TCL Group adheres to the established business strategy, continuously improves its competitiveness, and develops sustainably and healthily.
Based on the confidence in the company's future development and the maintenance of investors' interests, combined with the performance of the company's shares in the secondary market in the past year, and taking into account the company's operating conditions and financial conditions and other factors, the company plans to use its own funds, self-raised funds and other financing methods to repurchase the company's shares.
Yang Delong, chief economist of Qianhai Open Source Fund, said that the operation of listed companies to repurchase shares, on the one hand, can reduce the number of shares circulating in the market and increase the earnings per share of listed companies, which is an important positive for the stock price of the secondary market;
The repurchase of domestic listed companies has gradually increased in recent years, especially for high-performing stocks, and it is a very good way to boost investors' confidence through share repurchases, and it is also a practice worthy of recognition and encouragement.
