Qingyang, Gansu: Hu sheep come to "poverty alleviation".
The autumn of September renders the Loess Plateau.
In the Yimin Breeding Professional Cooperative in Yima Town, Xia Weili, a 58-year-old villager, filled the trough in the sheepfold with the last spade and forage, and stood by the trough to watch the white lake sheep chew carefully.
"It's delicious, and when it grows fat in autumn and winter, it can be sold at a good price. ”
Xia Weili said that he feeds the sheep "special nutritious meals" every day, cleans, sterilizes and disinfects regularly, and does not dare to slack off after careful service.
Xia Weili has been raising sheep for more than 20 years, and it was not until he came to work in the cooperative that he knew how extensive sheep herding was in the past.
Xia Weili is a native of Xiashuchi Village, Yima Town, Qingcheng County, Qingyang City, Gansu Province.
His neighbors are all sheep farmers, but they adhere to the traditional free-range method, and the quality of sheep is poor and the amount of sheep slaughtered is small.
In June this year, under the guidance of the government, 140 poor households in the village joined the cooperative, and everything began to change.
Xia Weili immersed himself in breeding all day long, because he always held back a lot of energy in his heart.
The people who have invested in the shares are all poor households, and they all trust their sheep to the cooperative, and they are counting on him whether they can distribute dividends and sell them at a high price at the end of the year.
Fortunately, with the guidance of technical personnel, he slowly learned to engage in epidemic prevention, mastered scientific feeding, and became one of the few breeding "good styles" in the village.
Yimin Breeding Cooperative is a standardized cooperative with a total of 16 sheep sheds and nearly 1,400 lake sheep.
Zou Tao, the person in charge of the cooperative, said that the standardized sheep shed is very doorway inside and out.
"The wool is thick and dense, easy to breed bacteria, the sheep can not stay in the hot and humid place, the sheep shed must be built in the place where the ditch is surrounded on three sides, and the fan must be installed to ventilate and dissipate heat. ”
Zou Tao said that in order to prevent the epidemic, it is also necessary to spray and disinfect the sheep shed regularly, and give the sheep three to four epidemic prevention shots in the first quarter.
In addition to living well, the "little sheep" also has to eat forage made of silage corn, wheat straw, alfalfa, etc., and have a wide enough "playground" to stretch their muscles.
The cooperatives adopt the method of trusteeship and substitution to guide local farmers to put the improved breeds of lake sheep here, and raise, manage and sell them in a unified manner, so as to realize the breeding, scientific, standardized and intensive breeding.
Today, the 140 poor households with sheep as shareholders have a dividend of more than 6,000 yuan per household every year, and there are 4 poverty alleviation targets who have registered for poverty alleviation and work in the cooperative.
From "grazing in the mountains" to "precision feeding", from "local mating" to "artificial insemination", from "looking at the body shape and touching the belly" to "doing B ultrasound one by one"... In Qingyang, Gansu Province, sheep breeding is not only a change in feeding methods, but also a change in the model of "leading enterprises + cooperatives + farmers" has changed the scene of "raising sheep on the hillside and selling sheep in the market", overcoming the weakness and scatterishness of traditional agriculture and animal husbandry, and the poor life of farmers has become better because of modern sheep raising.
Zou Tao said that if the market price is weak, the local leading enterprise Gansu Zhongsheng Agriculture and Animal Husbandry Development Co., Ltd. will buy at a market protection price of 27 yuan per kilogram to help farmers diversify market risks.
Xu Jianfeng, general counsel of Gansu Zhongsheng Agriculture and Animal Husbandry Development Co., Ltd., said that the company has driven more and more poor households to read the "Sheep Sutra" by providing loan guarantees, sheep supply, order breeding, quotation purchase, unified processing and sales and other services for poor households.
In Qingyang, at least 8,200 impoverished families have achieved a steady increase in income through forage breeding, improved seed breeding, large-scale breeding, slaughtering and segmentation, and market sales of Zhongsheng Agriculture and Animal Husbandry.
Qingyang City is located in the northern agriculture and animal husbandry ecotone, rich in forage resources.
At present, there are 913 large-scale sheep farms and cooperatives in the city, with more than 5 million sheep raised, and two processing production lines of 1.3 million sheep slaughtering scale have been built.
The French finance minister said that more than 10 billion euros will be cut in taxes next year and called on Germany to follow suit
PARIS, Sept 26 (Reuters) - France will cut taxes by more than 10 billion euros ($10.9 billion) next year, Finance Minister Bruno Le Maire said on Thursday, and Germany should keep pace with France's fiscal stimulus to revive the sluggish economy.
Introducing France's 2020 budget, Le Maire said the ECB's latest monetary easing measures have created an opportunity for the governments of those member states that can afford to increase investment.
The European Central Bank (ECB) cut interest rates to a record low on 12 September and plans to restart bond purchases to bring down borrowing costs, hoping to spur economic recovery and push up inflation.
"Low interest rates will not bring prosperity back to Europe, and monetary policy measures are necessary but not sufficient," Le Maire told reporters.
"Germany needs to invest, it needs now, and the sooner the better. Don't wait for the situation to get worse before acting," he added.
He has made this appeal to Germany on several occasions.
France has implemented more than 10 billion euros in tax cuts this year, which has given a big boost to France's economic growth.
The global economy has lost momentum, and the export-dependent German economy has borne the brunt.
Le Maire noted that the tax burden on French households will be reduced by 9.3 billion euros next year, including 5 billion euros in income tax relief.
In addition, with the gradual implementation of the corporate tax rate from 33.3% to 25% over a five-year period, the corporate tax burden will be reduced by almost 1 billion euros.
