British tourist car keys fell into the lake and the whole family was trapped in France for five days
Recently, a couple in Wales, England, took their two children on vacation to France, but accidentally dropped the car keys into the lake, and the family was forced to wait for five days to get the new keys prepared by the car manufacturer.
The couple then left France with their children.
According to reports, on September 16, local time, when the British family was visiting a lake in France, their daughter accidentally knocked over a leather bag and the car keys inside fell into the lake.
But it took them hours and they couldn't find the key.
And all their belongings and cash were locked in the car.
Despite the fact that the British tourist had purchased insurance before departure, the insurance company refused to help on the grounds that there was no danger of theft of the vehicle.
They hired a trailer to take the car to a garage for storage, and then reordered the keys from the car manufacturer.
A few days later, the British tourists finally got the prepared keys, and the couple left France with their children.
Their scheduled trip was cancelled due to the loss of their car keys.
