In the field of low-risk varieties of food production licenses, the notification and commitment system will be piloted, and the representative offices of foreign enterprises will be delegated to the free trade zone
On the 27th, the Shanghai Municipal Administration for Market Regulation and the Pudong New Area Government signed a memorandum of understanding to launch 20 market supervision reform measures, some of which are the first pilot measures in the country.
According to reports, the notification commitment refers to the administrative organ's one-time notification of the conditions and requirements stipulated by laws and regulations to the applicant in writing when handling the relevant license registration matters.
After the applicant signs the pledge, the administrative organ can directly handle it.
According to the memorandum, the Shanghai market supervision department will support the Pudong New Area and the Shanghai Pilot Free Trade Zone to pilot the notification and commitment system in three areas: enterprise name registration, simple process and low-risk food production license, and type approval of some measuring instruments, so as to make enterprise access more convenient.
Shanghai Shao Wansheng Food Co., Ltd. obtained the "Food Production License" on the spot by informing and promising on the 27th, becoming the first enterprise to enjoy the pilot dividend.
The person in charge of the enterprise said that the food license can also be obtained on the spot, and the method of "tolerant acceptance" has been adopted, that is, the enterprise is allowed to submit some materials within the time limit agreed in the notification commitment, "I really feel the convenience of the reform." ”
According to the Shanghai market supervision department, the implementation of the notification and commitment system for food production licenses is the first pilot in the country.
After the reform, the examination and approval process has been compressed from the previous 6 links of "registration, acceptance, on-site verification, sampling inspection, material review, and approval and certificate making" to 3 links of "registration, acceptance, and approval of the certificate", and the completion time has been shortened from 20 working days before the reform to the on-the-spot completion.
Taking into account the high degree of economic extroversion of Pudong, the Shanghai market supervision department has delegated the registration authority of the resident representative offices of foreign (regional) enterprises to the Shanghai Free Trade Zone, so as to facilitate the enterprises to handle the registration nearby.
Statistics show that a total of 1,592 permanent representative offices in the Shanghai Free Trade Zone have been involved in this decentralization, of which 99 have been handled in accordance with the new regulations.
