Starting next year, Chinese students can apply for German bachelor's degree with the results of the college entrance examination
Recently, the Anabin database, which is responsible for the evaluation and certification of foreign academic qualifications in Germany, announced on its official website that starting in 2020, Chinese high school graduates can directly apply for a bachelor's degree in German universities with their college entrance examination results, and do not need to register at domestic universities first.
Previously, Chinese high school graduates who wanted to apply for German universities needed to study for one semester (211,985 universities) or three semesters (general undergraduates) in China, and pass the APS audit or TestAS exam.
The release of the new regulations may save Chinese students who are interested in studying in Germany at least half a year.
It is reported that the new regulations will come into effect in the second half of 2019.
Applicants must meet the following requirements: complete 12 years of formal compulsory education, obtain a high school diploma, take the general examination and college entrance examination, and have a score of 70% or more (or 525 if the total score is 750), and include two language scores and one mathematics or natural science score.
In addition, the requirements for college entrance examination scores vary for specific majors.
For example, to apply for majors such as Pharmacy, Stomatology, Veterinary Medicine, Pharmacy, etc., the college entrance examination score must reach 80% of the full score, and the college entrance examination subjects must include at least two subjects in mathematics, physics, chemistry, and biology, or take the science comprehensive, and apply for law majors, the college entrance examination score must reach 80% of the full score, and the college entrance examination subjects must include at least two foreign languages, history, geography, or take the comprehensive study.
According to incomplete statistics, many countries, including Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, etc., recognize China's college entrance examination results.
Taking the UK as an example, universities such as the University of Cambridge, the University of Birmingham, and the University of Leicester all accept Chinese students to apply for admission based on their college entrance examination results.
