The Information Office of the State Council released a white paper entitled "China and the World in the New Era".
On the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, the Information Office of the State Council released a white paper on "China and the World in the New Era" on the 27th.
Xu Lin, deputy director of the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central Committee and director of the Information Office of the State Council, said that the white paper systematically introduces China's development achievements, development path and development trend, and elaborates on China's relationship with the world, so as to enhance the international community's knowledge and understanding of China's development.
The white paper points out that over the past 70 years, under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, China has undergone earth-shaking changes and created an unprecedented development miracle in human history.
Through a large number of data and facts, the white paper introduces the great achievements, great significance and contributions of China's development to the world over the past 70 years.
The white paper points out that in a few decades, China has completed the development process that developed countries have gone through for hundreds of years, and its total economic output has jumped to the second place in the world, and nearly 1.4 billion people have shaken off material shortages, and on the whole have reached the level of moderate prosperity, enjoying unprecedented dignity and rights.
The white paper stresses that over the past 70 years, the Chinese people have made a new world by starting from scratch, relying on themselves, and working hard; over the past 70 years, China has developed in connection and interaction with the world, embraced, learned, and contributed to the world; over the past 70 years, while realizing self-development, China has made contributions to world peace and injected impetus into the common development of all countries.
The white paper pointed out that the fundamental reason for China's successful development over the past 70 years is that under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, the Chinese people have found the correct development path of socialism with Chinese characteristics and unswervingly followed this path.
The white paper stresses that the path of socialism with Chinese characteristics is a path established based on the national conditions of the country, a path that puts the interests of the people first, a path of reform and innovation, a path of seeking common development in the course of opening up, and a path of comprehensively governing the country according to law.
China's development path is in line with China's national conditions, adapts to the requirements of the times, and will show more and more bright prospects for development as the times progress.
In response to the international community's concern about China's development, the white paper stresses that achieving national prosperity and strength, national rejuvenation and people's happiness is not only the dream of the Chinese people, but also the common dream of the people of all countries.
The white paper points out that China is the main stabilizer and power source of world economic growth, all-round opening up to the outside world has created more opportunities for the development of all countries, China has provided more public goods for the international community, and China's development has provided experience and reference for other developing countries.
Faced with the question of "what is wrong with the world and what should mankind do?", the white paper points out that the world today is in the midst of major changes unseen in a century, and human society is full of both hope and challenge.
China proposes to build a community with a shared future for mankind, opens up a new development path of win-win cooperation, joint contribution and shared benefits, and provides new options for human development.
The white paper calls on all countries to unite to build a new type of international relations, promote a new type of economic globalization, uphold the international system with the United Nations at its core, promote exchanges and mutual learning among civilizations, and jointly promote the building of a community with a shared future for mankind and a better world.
With China's increasing development, the international community is generally concerned about how the developed China gets along with the world.
The white paper points out that China's development is inseparable from the world, and the world's peace, development, prosperity and stability cannot be separated from China.
China has always placed its own development in the coordinate system of human development, adhered to win-win cooperation and common development, upheld and promoted economic globalization, actively developed global partnerships, firmly supported multilateralism, upheld international fairness and justice, promoted the high-quality development of the Belt and Road Initiative, actively participated in and led the reform and construction of the global governance system, and always been a builder of world peace, a contributor to global development, and a defender of the international order.
At present, China's development has entered a new era.
The white paper points out that in the new era, China's determination to take the road of socialism with Chinese characteristics will not change, its determination to learn from each other and achieve win-win cooperation with other countries will not change, and its determination to walk hand in hand with the world will not change.
The white paper concludes by pointing out that in today's world, the future and destiny of all countries have never been so closely linked.
The white paper "China and the World in the New Era" consists of a preface, a main text and a conclusion, with a full text of more than 29,000 words.
The white paper was published in eight languages, including Chinese, English, French, Russian, German, Spanish, Arabic and Japanese, and was published by the People's Publishing House and the Foreign Languages Publishing House, and distributed in Xinhua bookstores nationwide.
Is MCA contesting in the Johor state parliamentary by-election for Tanjung Piai?
