A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province was ordered to "patrol the mountains" for hunting wild animals
A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province, was sentenced to prison for hunting wild animals, and at the same time ordered to compensate 15,420 yuan (RMB, the same below) for the cost of repairing ecological resources and environmental damage.
Due to the poverty of the defendant's family, the procuratorate used alternative labor to compensate for the cost of ecological restoration, realizing the organic unity of legal and social effects.
Wang Zhongliang, deputy procurator general of the Baokang County Procuratorate, introduced on the 27th that through 3 months of alternative labor such as "voluntary patrols", the defendant Zhou has established a deep relationship with wild macaques, and feels deeply remorseful for his previous animal hunting.
On June 21 this year, a criminal attached civil public interest lawsuit in the field of ecological resources filed by the Baokang County Procuratorate was openly tried in the county court and the verdict was pronounced in court.
Defendant Zhou was sentenced to 3 years imprisonment, suspended for 4 years, and fined 3,000 yuan, and ordered to compensate 15,420 yuan for the restoration of ecological resources and environmental damage.
After investigation, Zhou began to set up a power grid at the cliff in late January 2014 and hunted more than 20 wild animals, including impalas, small muntjacs, hairy crowned deer, etc.
Impala is a national second-class endangered wild protected animal, and the small muntjac and hairy crowned deer are listed in the "National Terrestrial Wildlife Protection List".
During the trial, Zhou confessed to his illegal facts and behavior, and was willing to bear attached civil liability.
However, considering the poor economic situation of Zhou's family, under the coordination of the Baokang County Procuratorate, the local village committee, Lin Zhan, and Zhou reached an agreement on alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration costs: that is, Zhou provided public welfare labor services to compensate for ecological restoration costs by carrying out macaque domestication and management work, voluntary mountain patrols, and forest protection in the village macaque reserve for one year.
The court recognized the prosecutor's suggestion and agreed that while Zhou was executing a suspended sentence, he would actively fulfill the obligation of "alternative labor to compensate for the cost of ecological restoration".
At present, Zhou has been working on a voluntary basis in the macaque sanctuary for 3 months, actively patrolling the mountains and performing well.
In recent years, the Baokang County Procuratorate has organically integrated procuratorial functions and social governance behaviors in practice, scientifically using supervision methods such as procuratorial suggestions, investigation supervision, and litigation supervision, and minimizing the damage caused by criminal acts to the ecological environment with the help of judicial means.
UN awards Champions of the Earth Award to Ant Forest
Amid warm applause and magnificent music, Xu Di, the leader of the "Ant Forest" project, and Shen Junliang, the user representative, walked onto the podium and received the trophy of the 2019 United Nations "Champions of the Earth" award from the host.
The 2019 Champions of the Earth award ceremony was held in New York, USA on the 26th, and the "Ant Forest" project, which uses mobile phone mini programs to drive hundreds of millions of people to participate in environmental protection actions, won the "Incentive and Action Award".
A week earlier, the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) had announced the winners at its headquarters in Nairobi, Kenya, but the excitement of the ceremony was still unconcealed.
In an interview with Xinhua News Agency, Inger Andersen, Executive Director of the United Nations Environment Programme, said that the "Ant Forest" is an exciting innovation that has brought hundreds of millions of people into action to understand the environmental challenges facing humanity and what humans can do for the environment.
It uses technology to connect people and the environment, so that everyone can participate in the action to protect the planet, which will have a huge impact.
Launched in August 2016 by China's Ant Financial Services Group (Ant Financial) on the Alipay platform, "Ant Forest" allows users to accumulate "green energy" and "plant trees" on their mobile phones by recording their daily lives in green travel and paying utility bills online.
Every time a user grows a virtual tree, Ant Forest and its charity partners will plant a real tree in the desertified area.
As of August this year, 500 million "Ant Forest" users have reduced carbon emissions by 7.92 million tons, and 122 million trees have been planted in desertified areas.
Costa Rica was awarded the "Champions of the Earth" award on the same day for its national environmental efforts, and Costa Rican President Carlos Alvarado, who came to receive the award, praised the contribution of the "Ant Forest", "It is impressive to be able to inspire so many people to participate in green action".
Jing Xiandong, Chairman and CEO of Ant Financial, said that the Champions of the Earth Award is an affirmation of the "Ant Forest" project.
Technology and open platforms make it possible for everyone to participate in a low-carbon life, and this honor belongs to all participants.
Jing Xiandong said that in the past three years, the "Ant Forest" has affected 500 million people, and the goal of the "Ant Forest" in the next three years is to bring 1 billion people around the world to participate in low-carbon actions.
While preventing desertification and protecting the environment, they are also exploring how to make farmers' income come from more green mountains and clear waters.
In addition to providing employment opportunities through tree planting, it also hopes to help farmers increase their incomes through agricultural product development projects and e-commerce platforms.
The public welfare and environmental protection model based on digital technology created by "Ant Forest" has also successfully gone overseas and has been used as a reference by other countries.
In June this year, GCash, the largest "e-wallet" in the Philippines, launched the Philippine version of "Ant Forest" to encourage Filipino users to better protect the environment through low-carbon living.
According to reports, GCash will work with the Philippine Department of Environment and Natural Resources, environmental protection public welfare organizations, etc., and plans to plant 365,000 trees in the Philippines within one year of the project's launch.
The Champions of the Earth Award is the highest award in the field of environmental protection at the United Nations and is awarded annually.
The "Ant Forest" award is the third consecutive year that a green innovation project from China has won the "Incentive and Action Award", following the builder of China's Saihanba Forest Farm and the "Thousand Villages Demonstration and Ten Thousand Villages Remediation" project in Zhejiang Province, China.
Economic and trade frictions affect the "report card" of the U.S. economy.
The U.S. economic "report card" for the second quarter of this year showed that the growth rate of the U.S. gross domestic product (GDP) slowed significantly from the previous quarter, affected by the sharp decline in private sector investment and exports.
Analysts pointed out that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty they brought were the main reasons for the decline in private sector investment and exports in the second quarter.
The final revised data released by the U.S. Department of Commerce on the 26th showed that U.S. GDP grew at an annualized rate of 2% in the second quarter, the same as the previously announced revised data, but significantly lower than the 3.1% in the first quarter.
According to the data, consumption growth became the main factor supporting the growth of the US economy in the second quarter.
Personal consumption expenditures, which account for about 70% of the total U.S. economy, increased by 4.6% quarter-on-quarter, driving economic growth by 3.03 percentage points.
In addition, government consumption expenditure and investment drove economic growth by 0.82 percentage points.
However, private sector investment fell by 6.3 percent from the previous quarter in the second quarter, dragging down the economic growth of the quarter by 1.16 percentage points, while exports fell by 5.7 percent from the previous quarter, and net exports dragged down the economic growth of the quarter by 0.68 percentage points.
Barry Knapp, managing partner of Ironside Macroeconomic Consulting, said that private sector investment not only failed to maintain the momentum of last year's growth, but fell sharply, as economic and trade frictions and rising uncertainty hit business confidence.
Knapp believes that under the influence of policy uncertainty, U.S. corporate capital spending is expected to remain in a downward trend next year.
Analysts believe that although consumption growth has formed a strong support for the U.S. economy in the second quarter, there are more and more signs that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty brought by them have affected consumer confidence and adversely affected the outlook for U.S. consumption.
Richard Curtin, the head of the survey and a professor of economics at the University of Michigan, said a few days ago that in the latest survey, 38% of consumers spontaneously mentioned the negative impact of tariffs on the U.S. economy, a new high in a year and a half.
As for the future trend of the U.S. economy, analysts generally believe that the U.S. economy will continue to slow down.
However, some experts said that if economic and trade frictions are eased, the performance of the US industrial sector and financial markets will improve.
Kelyn Burch, a global economist at the Economist Intelligence Unit in the UK, predicts that the US economy will continue its gradual downward trend since the beginning of this year, and the growth rate will fall to a lower level than in the second quarter.
Mark Zandi, chief economist at Moody's Analytics, predicts that the U.S. economy will grow by 2.3 percent this year and slow further to 1.6 percent next year, assuming that economic and trade frictions do not continue to escalate.
Ellen Hutzen, investment manager at Putnam Investments, pointed out that the biggest concern of companies at present is the economic and trade disputes and the uncertainty they bring, and if the economic and trade disputes can be resolved, the uncertainty will be greatly reduced, and the performance of the industrial sector will be much better than it is now.
Matt Melly, equity strategist at Miller-Tabak Asset Management, said that economic and trade frictions are still the "primary problem" and the main reason for the sharp volatility in the U.S. capital market this year, and whether the economic and trade frictions can be properly resolved will be the key to affecting the direction of the U.S. capital market for the rest of the year.
Ningxia pioneered joint parental leave for couples, and parents of children aged 0 to 3 can take 10 days per year
Protecting women's legitimate rights and interests is an embodiment of respecting and protecting human rights, and is also an important symbol of social civilization and progress.
On September 27, at the 15th meeting of the Standing Committee of the 12th National People's Congress of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, the "Regulations on the Protection of Women's Rights and Interests of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region" was passed by a large majority.
This is the first provincial-level local regulation in Ningxia to comprehensively and systematically safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of women, which will be officially implemented on November 1, 2019.
It is understood that the "Regulations" adopted this time are revised on the basis of the 2007 "Measures for the Implementation of the Law of the People's Republic of China on the Protection of Women's Rights and Interests in Ningxia", which is divided into 9 chapters and 65 articles, including general provisions, political rights, cultural and educational rights, labor and social security rights, property rights, personal rights, marriage and family rights, legal responsibilities, and supplementary provisions.
In the "Regulations", Ningxia encourages the exploration of the implementation of joint parental leave between husband and wife, which is the first in the country.
In April this year, the General Office of the State Council promulgated the "Guiding Opinions on Promoting the Development of Infant and Child Care Services for Children Under the Age of Three", which has a relevant description of joint parenting between husband and wife.
In the process of revising the "Regulations", Ningxia innovatively proposed to "encourage employers to grant 10 days of joint parental leave to both husband and wife each year during the period between the children and the age of 3 for couples who have children in accordance with the provisions of laws and regulations".
At the same time, the Regulations highlight anti-sexual harassment and the protection of female minors.
Article 43 of the Regulations incorporates the latest legislative achievements in the personality rights section of China's current Civil Code, and provides detailed provisions on the constituent elements of sexual harassment, the subject and mechanism of counter-sexual harassment, etc.
Article 44 of the Regulations explicitly prohibits frequent incidents of sexual assault against girls, and requires educational institutions to carry out relevant education, protection and prevention work, becoming a new benchmark for the protection of girls in local legislation.
Article 35 of the Regulations clearly stipulates women's right to know about joint property and the obligations of property registration agencies and related subjects, so as to provide solid institutional support for women's rights protection.
In addition, in response to the hot issue of gender discrimination in employment, Article 26 of the Regulations not only prohibits direct discrimination, but also orders the prohibition of indirect discrimination, and absorbs the latest practical experience of joint interviews, strengthens the punishment of gender discrimination violations, and more effectively protects the legitimate rights and interests of women.
In recent years, the Ningxia Women's Federation, together with the Department of Public Security, Procuratorate, Civil Affairs and other departments, has achieved remarkable results in promoting and introducing social professional forces to participate in the mediation of marital and family conflicts and disputes and anti-domestic violence.
The Regulations summarize and improve this, and in a number of laws and regulations, they encourage the mobilization of social forces and the accumulation of social resources to jointly protect women's rights and interests, and require the people's governments at or above the county level to provide stable and institutional guarantees and support through the purchase of services and other means.
Academician Yuan Longping of Inner Mongolia Xing'an League, salt and alkali tolerant rice, and the yield of rice per mu exceeded 1,000 catties
The reporter learned from the Administrative Office of the Xing'an League of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region on the 27th that the "Xing'an League Academician Yuan Longping Workstation On-site Yield Measurement and Acceptance Appraisal Meeting" held by the league a few days ago came with good news, and the average yield of saline-alkali tolerant rice per mu exceeded 1,000 catties.
The yield measurement expert group composed of six experts from the Heilongjiang Academy of Agricultural Sciences, Yangzhou University and the Hunan Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs sampled and harvested the "Xingyan series" rice on the spot.
According to expert evaluation, the average yield of saline-alkali tolerant rice per mu in land with a pH value of 8.8 to 9.6 and a salinity content of 5‰ to 6‰ reached 508.8 kg.
Wang Shigang, executive director of the Yuan Longping Academician Workstation of the Xing'an League, said: "Our next step is to innovate and reform on the basis of this year's experiment, and cultivate and optimize the saline-alkali tolerant rice varieties again, so as to make the quality better and the yield higher." ”
Lai Yongcai, the leader of the yield measurement expert group, vice president and researcher of the Heilongjiang Academy of Agricultural Sciences, said: "Under the premise that the factors of production remain unchanged, I believe that we will continue to strengthen scientific and technological research, and saline-alkali tolerant rice will continue to produce miracles on saline-alkali land." ”
The Xing'an League belongs to the concentrated contiguous poverty-stricken areas at the southern foot of the Great Khing'an Mountains.
In October 2018, Yuan Longping Academician Workstation was unveiled in Xing'an League.
Academician Yuan Longping led a team of experts to speed up the introduction and promotion of the latest cultivation of "saline-alkali tolerant hybrid rice" varieties and advanced technology, and built a 960-acre saline-alkali tolerant rice base in the Horqin Right Wing Central Banner.
The on-site yield measurement of saline-alkali tolerant rice not only injected hope for the promotion of saline-alkali medium and low-yield fields in Xing'an League to medium and high-yield fields, but also provided a scientific basis for rice planting in saline-alkali land under the same conditions in China.
According to the Australian Network, after marathon debates and weeks of protests, on September 26, local time, New South Wales, Australia, passed the abortion legalization bill.
It is reported that the bill has sparked political debate in the past eight weeks, and since independent MP Greenwich announced the introduction of the bill, there have been serious divisions within the Australian Liberal Party.
According to the report, after nearly 40 hours of discussion, the Australian New Zealand Senate passed the abortion legalization bill by 26 votes to 14 on the evening of the 25th, making it the third longest bill in the NSW Senate.
On the morning of the 26th, after a final vote in the House of Representatives of NSW, abortion was legalized in NSW.
The bill allows women to terminate pregnancies at 22 weeks of pregnancy and also allows women to have an abortion later in pregnancy if two doctors agree.
The Senate passed an amendment on the evening of the 25th that doctors can seek advice from the multidisciplinary panel of the hospital advisory committee before performing an abortion for a woman after 22 weeks of pregnancy.
In addition, the amendments passed by the Senate include that doctors must provide proper care for babies who survive the termination of pregnancy.
The NSW Premier has faced public criticism from conservatives on the bill, and she did not attend the final vote after she stepped in on several occasions to buy more time for the bill.
Berry Jiklian defended his absence from the vote, saying: "I need to spend time managing the whole NSW. ”
It is reported that Davis, a Liberal MP from Australia, was once the strongest opponent of the abortion bill, and once threatened to quit the NSW government because of the bill, and said that the bill had triggered a "government crisis".
But after that, Davis made a concession.
Davis said: "The content of the amendment to the bill to legalize abortion, which was submitted to the House of Representatives on the morning of the 26th, actually provides more protections for women and doctors. ”
Meanwhile, Barilaro, leader of Australia's NSW National Party, said he was proud to be part of the government that legalised abortion.
"What we achieved last night was historic for NSW in that it legalised abortion, where abortion was no longer a crime and women who had abortions were not treated as criminals. ”
