Liu Kun, Minister of Finance: 67 central enterprises and financial institutions have transferred 860.1 billion yuan of state-owned assets to enrich the social security fund.
Liu Kun, Minister of Finance, said on the 27th that up to now, 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have completed the transfer of part of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund, with a total transfer of state-owned capital of about 860.1 billion yuan.
Liu Kun made the above statement at the national task deployment meeting for the transfer of part of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund jointly held by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, and the State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission on the same day.
"The transfer of part of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund, is an important measure to reform and improve the basic pension insurance system, is the development of state-owned enterprises to share the results of the whole people and the basic pension insurance system intergenerational fairness of the full embodiment, is a based on the current, taking into account the long-term policy measures. ”
In 2017, the State Council issued the "Implementation Plan for the Transfer of Part of the State-owned Capital to Enrich the Social Security Fund", requiring the selection of some central enterprises and some provinces to carry out pilot projects.
According to Liu Kun, the preliminary work of the transfer has achieved positive results.
At the central level, three batches of 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have been transferred, with a total of about 860.1 billion yuan of state-owned capital.
Among them, the transfer of central financial institutions in which the Ministry of Finance performs the duties of investors has been basically completed.
The transfer of central enterprises has a certain scale.
At the local level, the preliminary work of enterprise transfer has been carried out one after another.
By the end of 2018, the pilot work in Zhejiang and Yunnan provinces had been basically completed, with 15.8 billion yuan and 18.5 billion yuan of state-owned capital transferred respectively.
In addition to the pilot provinces, other provinces have also carried out preparatory work for the transfer, laying the foundation for the next step of the transfer.
According to the notice jointly issued by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, the State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission, the State Administration of Taxation and the China Securities Regulatory Commission, the transfer of part of the state-owned capital by the central and local governments to enrich the social security fund will be fully launched in 2019 and basically completed by the end of 2020.
The meeting held on the same day made specific arrangements for the comprehensive implementation of the transfer work.
The meeting stressed the need to complete the transfer work in a pragmatic and efficient manner.
"According to the schedule, the transfer work should be basically completed by the end of 2020.
The transfer work time is tight and the task is heavy. ”
Liu Kun said: All localities and departments should make meticulous organizations and careful arrangements to ensure that the transfer work is completed as required; promote the work in a down-to-earth manner, accurately grasp the content of the transfer policy; strengthen communication and coordination, and promptly resolve difficult problems.
State-owned assets transfer to enrich the social security fund - starting from the starting point of "enriching the social security fund money bag", the destination is to provide strong support for the old-age security.
However, the author believes that this is not a simple "physical displacement" of equity, but a "mathematical addition".
On September 20, the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, the State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission, the State Administration of Taxation and the China Securities Regulatory Commission jointly issued the "Notice on Comprehensively Promoting the Transfer of Part of the State-owned Capital to Enrich the Social Security Fund", clarifying the timetable for the transfer of state-owned assets to the social security fund, that is, the central and local transfer of part of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund will be fully launched in 2019.
After the document was released, the Ministry of Finance and other departments also implemented it quickly.
On September 25, the Ministry of Finance transferred 10% of the shares held by the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China and the Agricultural Bank of China to the Social Security Fund, with a total value of more than 115 billion yuan.
According to the regulations, the social security fund and other undertaking entities, as financial investors, enjoy the right to income, the right to dispose of and the right to know about the state-owned equity.
ICBC and ABC stated in the announcement that the change in equity will not lead to a change in the controlling shareholder and actual controller of the Bank.
In this regard, the author believes that similar equity transfer of state-owned enterprises is not a simple change of equity ownership, but an "addition operation" that can stimulate a series of effects.
The first step of the transfer of some state-owned assets to social security, the "addition result", can naturally reflect the ownership of state-owned enterprises and the sharing of development results.
After years of reform and development, most of the state-owned enterprises, especially the central enterprises, are in important industries and fields in China's economy, and the overall profitability is strong and stable.
Among them, the leading enterprises continue to achieve excellence, bigger and stronger.
On July 10, the executive meeting of the State Council decided to comprehensively promote the transfer of part of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund this year.
The Ministry of Finance immediately said that it would work with relevant departments, according to the deployment of the executive meeting of the State Council, to do a good job in comprehensively promoting the transfer of part of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund, fully reflecting the intergenerational fairness of the basic pension insurance system and the development of state-owned enterprises to share with the whole people.
The second step of the transfer, the "addition result", is to enhance the sustainability of China's social security fund and further consolidate the foundation of the pension and social security system.
With the aging of the population, China's social security funds are under pressure, and most of the state-owned assets as the main body of the transfer have the ability to make sustained profits and dividends, which can not only effectively supplement the social security fund, but also provide a source of living water for the social security fund.
Some estimates show that for every 3.8 percentage points of state-owned capital transferred, the contribution ratio of basic pension insurance of enterprises can be reduced by 1 percentage point.
The third step of the transfer, the "addition result", is to add a stabilizer to the capital market.
The way to obtain income from the main body of this transfer is "dividends as the mainstay, supplemented by operation".
As a financial investor of state-owned capital, the social security fund is indeed mainly based on equity dividend income.
However, as a value investor in the capital market, the social security fund has a strong capital operation ability.
For the listed assets in the state-owned capital, the participation of the social security fund in the shareholding will further optimize the corporate governance structure of listed enterprises, which is conducive to improving the level of enterprise operation and has a positive impact on listed companies and the capital market.
At the same time, as an investment vane, the increase in the weight of social security funds is conducive to further enhancing its influence in the market and playing a "stabilizer" role in the market.
In addition, it is also conducive to giving full play to the "value discovery" function of institutional investors and guiding investors to invest rationally and value.
At the age of 18, Karl Hartmann entered the Leipzig Conservatory, where he studied with Webern.
After the Nazis came to power, Hartmann first resisted by not publishing his works in Germany, and later even stopped writing.
In 1933, he composed the symphonic Miserae and dedicated it to "My Sleeping Friends".
In 1935, the symphony premiered in Prague, but was harassed by the Nazi bureaucracy.
After that, Hartmann was determined not to play any of his own compositions under the Nazis.
Hartmann's Funeral Concerto is a concerto for violin and strings when the manuscript of the piece was smuggled out of Germany for its premiere in Switzerland.
Listen to the funeral concerto performed by the Bern Chamber Orchestra at the Beethoven Festival in 2018.
The U.S. Senate approves Scalia as Secretary of Labor-Xinhuanet
Washington, September 26 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Senate voted on September 26 to approve President Trump's nomination of Eugene Scalia to be Secretary of Labor.
The vote was 53 in favor and 44 against, with no Democrats voting for Scalia.
Republicans believe Scalia's resume makes him a good fit for the post of labor secretary.
But in the eyes of Democrats, Scalia has long been on the opposite side of workers and unions during his career as a lawyer.
Scalia will succeed Alexandre Acosta.
Acosta, then Secretary of Labor, announced his resignation in July this year under huge public pressure after allegedly giving "leniency" to American billionaire Jeffrey Epstein for alleged sexual assault and trafficking of teenage girls.
Scalia, 56, is a partner at a well-known law firm in the United States, and his father is the late Justice Antonin Scalia of the U.S. Supreme Court.
The Department of Labor is a cabinet-level department of the U.S. federal government that oversees labor-related matters.
The White House also issued a statement on the same day saying that Trump had nominated Peter Geyner, acting administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, to formally lead the agency.
According to the procedure, Gainner's nomination must also be approved by the Senate.
The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is part of the U.S. Department of Homeland Security and coordinates federal government resources to deal with emergencies such as natural disasters and terrorist attacks in the United States and their aftermath.
