Italy's education minister has proposed a sugar tax to protect people's health.
Lorenzo Fioramonti, Minister of Education of Italy's new government and a member of the Five Star Movement, recently submitted a motion to parliament proposing that the Italian government implement a new tax policy on sugary drinks, snacks and air tickets.
According to reports, according to the bill motion proposed by Education Minister Fioramoni, the Italian government will impose a snack tax on sugary drinks, snacks and other unhealthy food and beverage goods, and at the same time impose a strict environmental tax on air tickets, with 1 euro for domestic flights and 1.5 euros for international flights.
Fiora Monti said that through this seemingly small series of tax measures, the Italian government is expected to receive 3 billion euros in tax revenue.
The proceeds of this tax will be used in the fields of education, health and environmental protection.
In response, Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte said he thought it was a viable option, while Italian parliamentarian, European parliamentarian and League leader Salvini tweeted sarcastically, asking everyone to hide desserts, biscuits, bread and sweets as soon as possible, because the new government is going to start a snack tax.
The report pointed out that the snack tax generally refers to a special tax on sugary drinks and high-calorie foods.
The imposition of this tax would contribute to the public health benefits.
On the evening of September 25, local time, the Chinese Embassy in Canada held a reception in Ottawa to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
Ottawa, September 26 (Reporter Yu Ruidong) Cong Peiwu, the new Chinese ambassador to Canada, held a reception in Ottawa on the evening of September 25 local time to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
Cong Peiwu said in his speech that since the founding of the People's Republic of China 70 years ago, under the strong leadership of the Communist Party of China and with the joint efforts of the people of the whole country, the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics has made achievements that have attracted worldwide attention, which has not only profoundly changed the face of China and benefited its own people, but also produced far-reaching world significance.
Based on its own national conditions, China has blazed a trail of socialism with Chinese characteristics, broadened the path for developing countries to modernize, and contributed Chinese wisdom and solutions to solving human problems.
The picture shows the guests stopping to watch the theme photo exhibition of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China held at the same time in the venue.
Cong Peiwu said that China has created a rare miracle in the history of human development in the world and made important contributions to promoting world peace and development.
China adheres to an independent foreign policy of peace, always advocates the basic norms governing international relations with the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence at its core, and is a builder of world peace, a contributor to global development and a defender of the international order.
China's development has provided new opportunities for the development of countries around the world, including Canada, and benefited the people of all countries.
Cong Peiwu stressed that the development of China-Canada relations over the past 50 years has shown that only by upholding the principles of equality and mutual respect can bilateral relations develop on the right track.
Otherwise, the relations between the two countries will suffer setbacks and the interests of the two countries will be damaged.
At present, China-Canada relations are experiencing serious difficulties, and the responsibility lies not with China.
"To untie the bell, you must tie the bell".
It is hoped that the Canadian side will come up with a proper solution to the outstanding problems in bilateral relations as soon as possible, so as to create conditions for the bilateral relations to return to the right track.
More than 700 Canadian government officials, federal senators, friends from all walks of life, diplomatic envoys in Canada, and representatives of overseas Chinese, Chinese-funded institutions and international students attended the reception.
Diplomats from the Chinese Embassy in Canada attended the reception, including Minister Counsellor Chen Mingjian and Minister Counsellor Heng Xiaojun.
A photo exhibition on the theme of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China was held at the reception, and promotional videos such as "China 2019" and "Beautiful China" were played.
Chinese and Canadian artists and diplomats from the embassies performed a unique cultural program.
This is also the first time that Cong Peiwu, the 16th Chinese ambassador to Canada, has appeared at a public event since taking office.
Cong Peiwu arrived in Canada on September 22 and presented a copy of his credentials to Wheeler, Chief of Protocol of Canada and Chief of Protocol of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, in Ottawa the following day.
Cong Peiwu, born in May 1967, graduated from China Foreign Affairs University.
He was resident at the Chinese Embassy in Canada at the beginning of this century.
Prior to his mission to Canada, he served as Director General of the Department of North America and Oceania at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China, and previously served as Minister Counsellor and Minister at the Chinese Embassy in the United Kingdom.
