Baidu's first fleet of robotaxis began trial operation
Yesterday, Baidu announced in Changsha that the trial operation of the Robotaxi fleet was officially launched.
The first batch of 45 Apollo and FAW Hongqi jointly developed the "Hongqi EV" Robotaxi fleet in Changsha and started trial operation in some of the open test sections in Changsha.
From now on, ordinary Changsha citizens can log on to the official website of Apollo to apply to become seed users and have the opportunity to test ride the experience.
One of the experience passengers said that he sat in the back of the vehicle, clicked on the screen in front of the passenger seat, and started the vehicle's autonomous driving trip with one click.
In the car, for the safety of passengers and the requirements of current policies and regulations, the trial operation vehicle is equipped with a safety officer in the driver's seat to maximize the safety of passengers.
In the process of driving, the vehicle can intelligently change lanes according to the road conditions, and can also judge the driving conditions of surrounding vehicles, and make automatic avoidance for short-range overtaking.
Throughout the experience, the screen in the passenger area shows the road conditions of pedestrians, cars, and even some traditional blind spots on the road in real time.
Even if the vehicle is blocked, you can see the traffic light changes ahead and the waiting time in advance, so you can see all the road conditions at a glance.
I've heard about autonomous driving on TV before, and I thought it was far away from us, but today I found it in our lives, and it feels amazing.
We look forward to it truly entering the lives of ordinary people in the future.
In June 2019, Apollo obtained 45 Manned Test Licenses issued by the Changsha Municipal Government.
At present, Changsha's autonomous driving test open road, passing through Changsha Artificial Intelligence Science and Technology City, Meixi Lake, Yanghu, Dawang Mountain, High-tech Zone and other sections, with a total length of 135 kilometers and a demonstration area of 70 square kilometers, is currently China's longest road mileage, the largest area, the most complex coverage scene, the most advanced vehicle-road collaborative infrastructure intelligent driving demonstration area.
It is expected that by the end of 2019, the Apollo Robotaxi fleet will cover about 50 kilometers of trial roads in Changsha, and in the first half of 2020, it is planned to cover 135 kilometers of roads currently open in Changsha.
