Jiangxi: "Line Chief" guards the safety of passenger line operation.
The reporter learned from the Jiangxi Provincial Highway Transport Administration that up to now, 1,334 passenger lines in 11 districts and cities in Jiangxi and 6 counties directly under the management of the province have "line lengths".
According to the person in charge of the Jiangxi Provincial Highway Transport Administration, due to the fact that the safety management of some passenger transport enterprises is a formality, the main responsibility of enterprise safety is not implemented, and violations of laws and regulations such as overcrowding and speeding of passenger vehicles and driver fatigue driving occur from time to time, and the road passenger safety situation is relatively grim.
In order to further consolidate the main responsibility of road passenger transport enterprises for safe production and ensure the safety of passengers, Jiangxi began to pilot the "line length system" in 2017 and gradually promoted it in the province in 2018.
At present, 92 road passenger transport enterprises in Jiangxi have implemented the "line length system", and selected 1,334 "line chiefs" to manage 1,334 lines, covering 4,824 operating buses.
According to reports, the "line chief" is generally designated by the road transport passenger transport enterprises to serve as a special person, specifically responsible for the management of the relevant line people, vehicles, lines and other work, to ensure that the person in charge of the line of the line, vehicles, drivers, operating environment, etc.
