Fujian Provincial Tax Treasury Bank Convenience Comprehensive Tax Payment Platform was officially launched-Chinanews.com
The Fujian Provincial Tax Treasury and Bank Convenience Comprehensive Tax Payment Platform was officially launched.
Fuzhou, September 27 (Ye Qiuyun) Fujian Provincial Tax Treasury Bank Convenience Comprehensive Tax Payment Platform was officially launched in Fuzhou City, Fujian Province on September 27.
The reporter learned that on October 26, 2018, the Fuzhou Central Sub-branch of the People's Bank of China, the Fujian Provincial Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation and China UnionPay Co., Ltd. jointly signed a memorandum of tripartite cooperation to create a comprehensive tax payment platform for the convenience of the people in Fujian Province.
After nearly a year of construction, at present, the platform has been successfully launched.
Wang Dehui, director of the Treasury Division of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People's Bank of China, introduced that the platform adheres to the construction concept of security, versatility, convenience, compliance and leadership, and connects the front end of taxation, government, banks, non-bank payment institutions and social service parties, and provides a variety of online and offline tax payment channels such as mobile APP, WeChat public account, tax hall, bank outlets, and inclusive financial service points, and the back end connects the national treasury and tax system.
It is reported that the platform brings together a number of projects to benefit the people and facilitate the people, among them, the medical insurance premium payment project for urban and rural residents has been officially launched.
The project has opened up 14 online and offline channels, providing services to more than 30 million urban and rural residents in Fujian Province, covering 76% of the permanent population of Fujian Province.
Medical premiums can be paid online through "Min Shui Tong" and "UnionPay", as well as the apps and WeChat official accounts of various banks, and offline medical premiums can be paid at various tax halls and rural inclusive financial service points in Fujian Province by scanning the code, waving the card, swiping the card and other methods.
Shi Dong, deputy governor of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People's Bank of China, said that the successful launch of the platform can provide the public with safe, efficient, multi-channel and multi-mode convenient tax payment services while ensuring the direct payment of government income into the warehouse and real-time interaction of data information.
At present, more than 9,000 of the more than 16,000 inclusive financial service points in the province have opened the function of checking and paying medical premiums, so that rural residents can check and pay medical premiums with peace of mind without leaving the village, so that the public has a stronger and stronger "sense of gain" and "happiness".
According to statistics, since the preliminary trial operation of the platform's medical insurance premium payment project for urban and rural residents for 20 days, the service users have reached 840,000, including 750,000 online payment users and nearly 20,000 inclusive financial service users.
In addition, Lin Guojing, deputy director of the Fujian Provincial Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, revealed at the event that the platform is the first in the country to apply blockchain electronic payment voucher technology.
Starting from next month, after completing the payment, the payer can also download the stamped electronic payment voucher directly through the mobile phone.
Fujian's tax information network based on blockchain technology is being built, and the "highway" of convenient tax payment will be further broadened.
