"One delivery has been" two UHV projects put into operation
On the 26th, the 1100 kV UHV DC transmission project and the Sutong 1000 kV AC UHV GIL comprehensive pipe gallery project were put into operation from Zhundong to ±southern Anhui.
These two projects occupy the commanding heights of the world's power transmission technology in their respective fields, and will greatly improve China's large-scale energy optimization allocation after they are put into operation.
Guo Zhi, chief economist of the National Energy Administration, said that the Zhundong to southern Anhui project is the world's largest transmission capacity and the farthest transmission distance.
Its operation is of great significance to promote the development of Xinjiang's energy base and ensure the power supply in East China.
GIL, or Gas Insulated Metal Enclosed Transmission Line.
The Sutong Pipe Corridor Project has created a record of the highest voltage level and the strongest transmission capacity in the world for the GIL project, and has realized the 'AC double ring network' with the highest voltage level of the backbone power grid in East China.
According to the State Grid Corporation, the transmission distance from Zhundong to southern Anhui is 3,324 kilometers.
If conventional technology is adopted, more than 15% of the electric energy will be lost on the way, and the project has been researched and developed, so that the economic transmission distance has been greatly increased to more than 3,000 kilometers.
After the project from Zhundong to southern Anhui is put into operation, 100 million kWh of electricity can be transmitted every 8 hours and 20 minutes, which can help solve the problem of absorbing existing new energy in Xinjiang.
According to the full load estimate, the annual power transmission of this line alone will reach 600 to 85 billion kilowatt hours, which can meet more than half of Shanghai's annual electricity consumption.
Sutong GIL comprehensive pipe gallery project is a control project of UHV AC ring network across the Yangtze River.
If the conventional overhead line is used to cross the river, two giant towers of more than 450 meters will need to be erected on the surface of the Yangtze River, and an artificial island of more than four football fields will be built for each tower.
In this regard, the State Grid has made bold innovations and developed a compact ultra-high voltage AC GIL transmission technology, which crosses the river from underwater through a tunnel to avoid the impact on the golden waterway.
The two projects have promoted a new leap in China's electrical equipment manufacturing capacity.
At present, the State Grid has built a total of "10 interchanges and 11 straight" UHV projects, and "4 interchanges and 3 straights" are under construction.
Foreign Exchange Bureau: China's Foreign Debt Structure Continues to Optimize The stability of foreign debt has been enhanced
On the whole, the structure of China's foreign debt has been continuously optimized, and the stability of foreign debt has been enhanced. ”
Wang Chunying, spokesperson and chief economist of the State Administration of Foreign Exchange, said on the 27th that the main indicators of China's foreign debt are within the internationally recognized safety line, and the risk of foreign debt is generally controllable.
Wang Chunying made the above remarks when the foreign exchange bureau released the external debt data at the end of June 2019 on the same day, and answered a reporter's question.
According to the data, as of the end of June 2019, China's full-caliber (including domestic and foreign currencies) external debt balance was US$1,998 billion, an increase of US$26.3 billion, or 1.3%, from the end of March 2019, mainly due to the growth of debt securities balance.
In the second quarter of 2019, more than 70% of China's full-caliber foreign debt increase was driven by non-residents' purchases of onshore RMB bonds, and non-residents were mainly medium and long-term investors such as the central bank.
At the end of June 2019, the proportion of medium- and long-term external debt increased by 3 percentage points from the end of March 2019, and the proportion of local currency external debt increased by 1 percentage point from the end of March 2019.
Wang Chunying said that with the inclusion of China's domestic RMB bonds in the Bloomberg Barclays Global Aggregate Index in April 2019, international investors' recognition of China's bond market has further improved, and they have continued to increase their holdings of domestic RMB bonds.
"China's balance of payments remains generally balanced, and the risk of external debt is controllable. ”
The reporter learned from the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences on the 27th that at present, fall armyworm in Yunnan has been effectively prevented and controlled, and no large-scale outbreaks have been caused, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In January this year, fall armyworm was first detected in Jiangcheng County, Pu'er City, Yunnan Province, and then confirmed in 129 counties in Yunnan, and the fall armyworm gradually spread from Yunnan to Chinese mainland, posing a direct threat to China's grain production.
Fall armyworm is a polyphagous long-distance migratory important agricultural pest native to tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas, and is a major migratory pest of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO) for global warning, with the characteristics of "international, migratory, explosive and destructive".
The pest harms more than 80 crops such as corn, sugarcane and sorghum, and can cause up to 70% yield loss due to large feed quantities.
It is difficult to control and control, and there is no registered pesticide for the control of this insect in China.
Since the invasion of fall armyworm into Yunnan, the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences selected researcher Chen Aidong to lead the provincial innovation team of the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences to go to the front line, conduct field investigations, collect samples, and carry out technical guidance and experimental demonstrations.
Chen Aidong's team has preliminarily grasped the population characteristics, natural enemy insect resources, overseas insect source characteristics, population migration trajectory, pesticide virulence and field control effect of fall armyworm in Yunnan.
Through the implementation of new green prevention and control technologies such as population monitoring, adult trapping, scientific medication and agronomic measures, the prevention and control effect in the demonstration area has reached more than 90%, and at the same time the use of chemical pesticides has been reduced, natural enemy resources and ecological environment have been protected, and technical support has been provided for the effective control of fall armyworm outbreaks and sustainable management in Yunnan.
At present, fall armyworm in Yunnan has been effectively prevented and controlled, and no large-scale outbreaks have been caused, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In the next step, the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences will focus on the ecological mechanism of population migration and invasion outbreaks, and break through the construction of biological control and green prevention and control technology systems.
At the same time, we will actively promote cross-border international cooperation, and strive to establish joint key laboratories and joint monitoring networks and demonstration areas overseas, so as to improve the all-round monitoring and early warning capabilities of fall armyworm in Yunnan.
