Textile representatives from 45 countries and regions jointly issued the "World Cloth Merchants Declaration".
On the 27th, at the 2nd World Cloth Merchants Conference 2019 held in Keqiao District, Shaoxing City, Zhejiang Province, representatives of the textile industry from 45 countries and regions jointly issued the "World Cloth Merchants Declaration".
The declaration pointed out that in the future, relevant countries will adhere to openness and collaboration, science and technology-driven, and fashion leaps, and will work together to promote the high-quality development of the world's textile industry.
This year's World Cloth Merchants Conference gathered about 1,200 representatives of the textile industry from 45 countries and regions to explore the sustainable development and win-win cooperation of the global textile industry around the textile industry trend in the world economic pattern.
Sun Ruizhe, president of the China National Textile and Apparel Council, said that the current global industrial division of labor, trade pattern, and innovation pattern are undergoing profound adjustments, and the textile industry has entered a new stage of globalization, innovation, and responsible development, and the development concept of "science and technology, fashion, and green" is deepening day by day.
Standing at the "crossroads" of global textile transformation and upgrading, Sun Ruizhe said, "To achieve sustainable development and common prosperity of the industry, global textile people need to actively participate, give their own strengths and share benefits. ”
At the meeting, representatives of the textile industry from 45 countries and regions jointly issued the "World Cloth Merchants Declaration" and jointly expounded the development goals and visions of the global textile industry.
The "World Cloth Merchants Declaration" pointed out that in the future, relevant countries will adhere to openness and coordination, continue to promote the interconnection of industries and markets, and jointly improve the development level of the industrial chain; will adhere to science and technology-driven, and constantly strengthen basic research, applied research and technology transformation, and jointly enhance the basic capacity of the industry; will focus on fashion jumps, give full play to the role of textile and garment as a cultural carrier and civilization bridge, and jointly enhance the cultural value of the industry.
Loureno Bartholomei, President of the Brazilian Association of Fashion Designers, said in an interview that the release of the "World Cloth Merchants Declaration" will help various countries to jointly improve the development level of the textile industry chain and achieve sustainable development of the textile industry.
For example, Loureno Bartholomei said that the Brazilian Association of Fashion Designers has more than 130 high-end local ready-to-wear brands, and designers are committed to designing fashionable and high-end ready-to-wear products, and Keqiao has a variety of high-quality fabrics. ”
As the venue of the World Cloth Merchants Conference, Keqiao has the world's largest textile market, and is currently gradually building a new pattern of upgrading internally and expanding and opening up to the outside world with its unique textile industry chain, representing China's textile image at the forefront of the world.
Shen Zhijiang, secretary of the Keqiao District Party Committee, said that Keqiao will take this cloth business conference as an opportunity to promote the textile industry to move forward in a more open, inclusive, inclusive, balanced and win-win direction with the attitude of a pioneer.
The central price of the renminbi calculated by Reuters is expected to open around 7.0883 yuan, with a countercyclical impact of 460 points.
According to Reuters' calculations based on the RMB exchange rate formation mechanism announced by the China Foreign Exchange Trade System (CFETS), the central parity of the yuan against the US dollar is expected to open around 7.0883 yuan on Friday, depreciating by about 154 points from the previous day.
The RMB closed at 7.1315 against the US dollar at the spot last day, while the central parity was 7.0729 yuan.
According to the pricing mechanism, a 586-point decline in today's median price movement reflects the impact of market supply and demand, another 27-point decline reflects the number of points required for a basket of exchange rates to remain largely unchanged overnight, and a 460-point increase reflects the impact of "countercyclical factors".
Reuters calculated that the central parity of the renminbi against the US dollar on the previous day was 7.0947 yuan, which was 218 points different from the actual value announced by the foreign exchange trading center.
Last day, Reuters calculated according to the mid-price released by CFETS, the RMB exchange rate CFETS index, the reference SDR (Special Drawing Rights) basket index and the reference BIS (Bank for International Settlements) basket index were 91.26, 91.46 and 94.92 respectively.
Tianjin Chow Tai Fook, the tallest building in northern China, was completed and more than 100 national patent achievements were created
The completion ceremony of Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Finance Center, the tallest building in northern China, was held in Tianjin Binhai New Area on the afternoon of the 26th, marking the success of the collaborative management platform of high-precision BIM model, a high-precision BIM model independently developed by the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Finance Center Project Department of China Construction Eighth Engineering Bureau, which won the Global Excellence Award in the global engineering construction industry.
Tianjin CTF Finance Centre is located in the Tianjin Economic and Technological Development Zone, with a total construction area of 390,000 square meters, 4 underground floors, 100 floors above ground, and a building height of 530 meters.
According to the relevant person in charge of the project department of Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Financial Center of China Construction Eighth Bureau, the steel consumption of the entire project exceeds 70,000 tons, the high-altitude group is about 376,000 meters of welds, which is equivalent to the height of Mount Everest, and the use of welding wire can circle the earth 40 times, and the number of steel components reaches 42,000, more than 50% of which are non-standard components, including the world's largest single-layer twisting angle of 90 degrees of double-tube elliptical section steel pipe column.
The complexity and processing difficulty of the steel structure of Tianjin Chow Tai Fook project is unprecedented.
According to industry insiders, Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Finance Center has taken the lead in implementing Building Information Modelling (BIM) management in an all-round way among the skyscraper projects that have been completed or are under construction in the country.
Creatively proposed and successfully implemented the "three-full BIM application" model of full participation, full professional application and whole process implementation, and developed a collaborative management platform based on high-precision BIM model.
The person in charge said that during the construction process of Chow Tai Fook, the project department first carried out BIM construction in the virtual world, and then carried out physical construction after scientific and error-free verification, so as to eliminate the problems of demolition, alteration and rework that may occur in the construction of previous construction projects in the bud.
In 2017, the BIM innovation of the Chow Tai Fook Finance Centre project won the first prize in the construction group of the Global Engineering Construction Industry Global Excellence Award at the Global AU Master Gathering and the 2017 Global Engineering and Construction Industry Global Excellence Award Ceremony.
During the construction of the project, the project department has created more than 130 national patent achievements.
It is worth mentioning that the BIM innovation achievements and technological innovation promotion of Tianjin Chow Tai Fook project not only made all the complex and numerous construction links achieve one-time excellence, shorten the construction period by more than four months, but also led to a significant improvement in safety management.
Not long ago, the Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Finance Center project also won the 2019 ISA International Security Award.
The 86th China-Laos-Myanmar-Thailand-Mekong joint patrol law enforcement was completed.
The reporter learned from the Information Office of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department on the 27th that at 15:30 on the same day, three Chinese law enforcement boats and two Laos law enforcement boats participating in the 86th China-Laos-Myanmar-Thailand-Mekong joint patrol law enforcement successfully berthed at China's Guanlei Port, marking the successful conclusion of the joint patrol and law enforcement operation.
The operation was launched in Guanlei Port on the 24th, lasted 4 days and 3 nights, and China, Laos, Myanmar and Thailand sent a total of 136 law enforcement officers and 6 law enforcement boats.
During the operation, the formation carried out joint patrols, anti-narcotics propaganda and other activities in key waters such as the Golden Triangle, Banxiangguo and Mengmo in Laos.
In addition, China has also sent a delegation of police instructors to the 122nd and 133rd border defense companies of the Lao People's Army to carry out exchanges on police combat skills, effectively enhancing the emergency response capability of law enforcement team members of the two sides to jointly deal with emergencies.
China, Laos, Myanmar and Thailand also held a law enforcement cooperation and exchange meeting in Chiang Saen, Thailand, to brief each other on the recent situation of the countries in border management, the fight against drug-related crimes, and the public security situation in the Mekong River Basin, and to hold consultations and exchanges on strengthening information exchange, research and judgment, and law enforcement cooperation, and reached a consensus.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Water Patrol Corps of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department, after the operation, China and Laos will continue to carry out a 10-day joint training and sectional joint patrol mission to improve the police detection rate in the Mekong River and make every effort to maintain the safety and stability of the Mekong River Basin.
The Thai commander said that since the launch of the Mekong River joint patrol and law enforcement, China, Laos, Myanmar and Thailand have maintained close exchanges, deepened practical cooperation, and achieved fruitful results in law enforcement, security cooperation and cultural exchanges.
It is hoped that the law enforcement cooperation between the four countries will continue to deepen and expand, strive to open up a new chapter in law enforcement cooperation among the four countries, and make new contributions to maintaining the security and stability of the Mekong River Basin.
