Zhang Ziyi of the 2019 Tokyo International Film Festival served as the jury leader
Chinese Herald NewsThe film "Under the White Clouds" directed by Wang Rui, a professor at Beijing Film Academy, as the only Chinese-language film, was shortlisted for the main competition unit of the 32nd Tokyo International Film Festival, which opened on October 28, and will compete for the highest award of the Tokyo International Film Festival - the Golden Kirin Award along with 13 other shortlisted films.
"Under the White Clouds" is the fifth film directed by Professor Wang Rui of "The World is Full of Peach and Plum", which tells the story of an ordinary Mongolian herdsman couple who have a certain life dilemma due to different life pursuits, starring Mongolian actors Jiri Mutu and Tana.
It is reported that "Under the White Clouds" held two world premieres during this film festival, with release dates on October 31 and November 3 respectively.
The 32nd Tokyo International Film Festival is scheduled to be held from October 28 to November 5 this year, in Roppongi, Hibiya and other venues in Tokyo, and on the afternoon of September 26, the organizing committee of the film festival held a press conference to officially announce the main competition unit of the Golden Kirin Award, the "Future of Asia" unit, the "Special Reception Works", Japanese Cinema Splash, "World Focus" and other units and projects.
The person in charge of the selection of competition films introduced the Chinese film "Under the White Clouds".
Zhang Ziyi served as the chairman of the international jury of the main competition unit of the film festival.
The "Asian Future" section has 3 Chinese-language films
In a series of sections of the Tokyo International Film Festival, its importance is second only to the "Asian Future" section of the main competition, although there are only 8 shortlisted films, 6 fewer than the main competition, but 3 Chinese-language films from Chinese mainland and Hong Kong are shortlisted.
The two Hong Kong films are "Baby's Revenge" directed by Luk Yixin, "Wheat Passerby" directed by Huang Qingxun starring actor Aaron Kwok and actress Miriam Yeung, and one mainland film is "Summer Night Knight" directed by You Xing.
In addition, the Sino-Japanese cooperative action-adventure film "Ice Storm", directed by Yu Fei and starring Hiroshi Yasho, Zhang Jingchu and Lin Bohong, will also be screened at this film festival as a "special reception work".
Alice Hirose, the spokesperson of the film festival and the "goddess", was absent from the press conference for some reason and delivered a video speech.
Famous director Yoji Yamada.
At the press conference, Hiroyasu Ando, chairman of the Tokyo International Film Festival, who just took office in August this year, Takero Hiroshi Hisamatsu, director of the film festival, and the person in charge of the selection of each unit took the stage to deliver speeches and introduce the purpose of the film festival and the films screened.
As a special guest at the press conference, Yoji Yamada, director of the 50th film in the "Injiro" series, "The Story of Injiro: Welcome Back", two Japanese film directors who were shortlisted for the main competition unit, Shin Tezuka ("Baro Bora") and Shin Adachi ("Comedy Wife Story"), and famous playwright and screenwriter Kazuki Nakajima, also appeared at the press conference to talk about their feelings about participating in the Tokyo Film Festival.
The international jury for the main competition is composed of five members, the chairman of the jury is Zhang Ziyi of China, and the other four are American producer Bill Gerber, French actor and producer Julie Gayer, Danish director Michael Knoll, and Japanese director Ryuichi Hiroki.
In addition, TIFFCOM (International Cinematographic Market), which was held in conjunction with the Tokyo International Film Festival, was held at the Sunshine City Convention Center in Ikebukuro from October 22 to 24, and this year there will be a record 401 group exhibits, especially 90 exhibitors from China, a 6.4-fold increase compared to 14 last year.
To this end, TIFFCOM designated October 22, the opening day, as "CHINA DAY", held a number of lectures, seminars, etc., and invited Japanese director Yuya Ishii to participate in related events, and the welcome dinner that night was also co-hosted by China and Japan.
Chengdu "Panda Planet" and the expansion project of giant panda breeding research base started
Chengdu, Sept. 27 (Xinhua) -- Enriching the giant panda culture-themed tourism routes, the panda base can accommodate 180 giant pandas in the future. The expansion project of "Panda Planet" and Giant Panda Breeding Research Base officially started in Chengdu on the 25th, which means that the "Panda Capital" project planned to be built in Chengdu was officially launched.
According to the plan, the "Panda Capital" built by Chengdu is composed of three areas: Beihu Area, Dujiangyan Area and Longquanshan Area, covering an area of 69 square kilometers.
The plan organically combines the ecological and cultural value of giant pandas with the construction of a beautiful and livable park city in Chengdu to create an ecological home for giant pandas.
"Panda Planet" belongs to the Beihu area, covering an area of 35 square kilometers, and combined with industrial planning, it will form a regional spatial structure of "1+N+X".
1 core attraction is the reconstruction and expansion project of the giant panda breeding research base, N cultural tourism consumption scenes, namely Panda Town, Xiaoyao Garden, Dream Garden, etc., and X regional infrastructure facilities.
After the reconstruction and expansion of the Chengdu Giant Panda Breeding Research Base, the scale will reach 3,525 acres, and the overall positioning is a world-class giant panda conservation demonstration site, and a place where people and animals can share good times.
The park is planned to accommodate 180 giant pandas and their companions (red pandas and golden monkeys).
