Solicitation of opinions on the new regulations: Social capital must have qualifications to obtain rural land management rights
Social capital must have qualifications to obtain rural land management rights
The "Administrative Measures for the Circulation of Rural Land Operation Rights" is open for public comment It is proposed to supervise the circulation of social capital such as industrial and commercial enterprises to obtain land operation rights
Yesterday, the website of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs issued a notice on the "Administrative Measures for the Circulation of Rural Land Management Rights (Revised Draft for Solicitation of Comments)" (hereinafter referred to as the "Draft") for public comment, increasing the supervision and risk prevention of industrial and commercial enterprises and other social capital circulation to obtain land operation rights.
The "Draft Opinions" are open to the public for comments today.
According to the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, in order to implement the newly revised "Rural Land Contracting Law", further consolidate and improve the basic rural management system, deepen the reform of the rural land system, and implement the "separation of powers" system, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs revised the "Administrative Measures for the Circulation of Rural Land Contracting and Management Rights" and formed the "Opinion Draft".
A reporter from Beijing Youth Daily learned that there are many important revisions to the "Draft Opinions" released for the first time.
The newly revised Rural Land Contract Law clarifies the scope of land circulation, implements the concept of "separation of powers", and sets up "land contracting and management rights" and "land management rights" in a special section, making a clear distinction between the transfer and exchange of land contracting and management rights and the circulation of land management rights (leasing, subcontracting, shareholding or other means).
In the Draft Opinions, in order to implement the concept of "separation of powers", effectively respond to the gist of the amendment to the Rural Land Contract Law, and take into account the great differences between the transfer of land management rights and the exchange and transfer of land contract management rights in terms of parties, procedures, supervision, etc., the revised draft defines the scope of circulation, focuses on the circulation of land operation rights, and the circulation methods include leasing and shareholding, and amends the name of the regulations from the Administrative Measures for the Circulation of Rural Land Contracting and Management Rights to the Administrative Measures for the Circulation of Rural Land Management Rights.
For the transfer and exchange of land contracting and management rights, separate administrative measures will be promulgated.
The Draft Opinion points out that in the context of the "separation of powers", farmers only have the right to operate land for a certain period of time.
Theoretically speaking, even in the event of bankruptcy liquidation, the peasants only have the risk of losing their management rights for a certain period of time, so it is no longer necessary in legal theory to stipulate that the contracted land should be returned to the original contractor, and it is also in conflict with the Bankruptcy Law.
In view of the problem of preventing the risk of peasants losing land, in practice, methods such as preferred shares, lease-to-shares, and buy-back have been developed.
Considering that preferred shares have been discussed in a relatively mature theory in the Company Law, it is suggested that they should be used as an advocacy provision to prevent the risk of losing land in shares.
